36static inline bool isIntegerOrPtr(MVT VT) {
37 return VT.isInteger() || VT == MVT::iPTR;
38}
39static inline bool isFloatingPoint(MVT VT) {
40 return VT.isFloatingPoint();
41}
42static inline bool isVector(MVT VT) {
43 return VT.isVector();
44}
45static inline bool isScalar(MVT VT) {
46 return !VT.isVector();
47}
48
49template <typename Predicate>
50static bool berase_if(MachineValueTypeSet &S, Predicate P) {
51 bool Erased = false;
52 // It is ok to iterate over MachineValueTypeSet and remove elements from it
53 // at the same time.
54 for (MVT T : S) {
55 if (!P(T))
56 continue;
57 Erased = true;
58 S.erase(T);
59 }
60 return Erased;
61}

63// --- TypeSetByHwMode
64
65// This is a parameterized type-set class. For each mode there is a list
66// of types that are currently possible for a given tree node. Type
67// inference will apply to each mode separately.
68
69TypeSetByHwMode::TypeSetByHwMode(ArrayRef<ValueTypeByHwMode> VTList) {
70 for (const ValueTypeByHwMode &VVT : VTList) {
71 insert(VVT);
72 AddrSpaces.push_back(VVT.PtrAddrSpace);
73 }
74}
75
76bool TypeSetByHwMode::isValueTypeByHwMode(bool AllowEmpty) const {
77 for (const auto &I : *this) {
78 if (I.second.size() > 1)
79 return false;
80 if (!AllowEmpty && I.second.empty())
81 return false;
82 }
83 return true;
84}
85
86ValueTypeByHwMode TypeSetByHwMode::getValueTypeByHwMode() const {
87 assert(isValueTypeByHwMode(true) &&
88 "The type set has multiple types for at least one HW mode");
89 ValueTypeByHwMode VVT;
90 auto ASI = AddrSpaces.begin();
91
92 for (const auto &I : *this) {
93 MVT T = I.second.empty() ? MVT::Other : *I.second.begin();
94 VVT.getOrCreateTypeForMode(I.first, T);
95 if (ASI != AddrSpaces.end())
96 VVT.PtrAddrSpace = *ASI++;
97 }
98 return VVT;
99}
100
101bool TypeSetByHwMode::isPossible() const {
102 for (const auto &I : *this)
103 if (!I.second.empty())
104 return true;
105 return false;
106}
107
108bool TypeSetByHwMode::insert(const ValueTypeByHwMode &VVT) {
109 bool Changed = false;
110 bool ContainsDefault = false;
111 MVT DT = MVT::Other;
112
113 SmallDenseSet<unsigned, 4> Modes;
114 for (const auto &P : VVT) {
115 unsigned M = P.first;
116 Modes.insert(M);
117 // Make sure there exists a set for each specific mode from VVT.
118 Changed |= getOrCreate(M).insert(P.second).second;
119 // Cache VVT's default mode.
120 if (DefaultMode == M) {
121 ContainsDefault = true;
122 DT = P.second;
123 }
124 }
125
126 // If VVT has a default mode, add the corresponding type to all
127 // modes in "this" that do not exist in VVT.
128 if (ContainsDefault)
129 for (auto &I : *this)
130 if (!Modes.count(I.first))
131 Changed |= I.second.insert(DT).second;
132
133 return Changed;
134}
135
136// Constrain the type set to be the intersection with VTS.
137bool TypeSetByHwMode::constrain(const TypeSetByHwMode &VTS) {
138 bool Changed = false;
139 if (hasDefault()) {
140 for (const auto &I : VTS) {
141 unsigned M = I.first;
142 if (M == DefaultMode || hasMode(M))
143 continue;
144 Map.insert({M, Map.at(DefaultMode)});
145 Changed = true;
146 }
147 }
148
149 for (auto &I : *this) {
150 unsigned M = I.first;
151 SetType &S = I.second;
152 if (VTS.hasMode(M) || VTS.hasDefault()) {
153 Changed |= intersect(I.second, VTS.get(M));
154 } else if (!S.empty()) {
155 S.clear();
156 Changed = true;
157 }
158 }
159 return Changed;
160}
161
162template <typename Predicate>
163bool TypeSetByHwMode::constrain(Predicate P) {
164 bool Changed = false;
165 for (auto &I : *this)
166 Changed |= berase_if(I.second, [&P](MVT VT) { return !P(VT); });
167 return Changed;
168}
169
170template <typename Predicate>
171bool TypeSetByHwMode::assign_if(const TypeSetByHwMode &VTS, Predicate P) {
172 assert(empty());
173 for (const auto &I : VTS) {
174 SetType &S = getOrCreate(I.first);
175 for (auto J : I.second)
176 if (P(J))
177 S.insert(J);
178 }
179 return !empty();
180}

182void TypeSetByHwMode::writeToStream(raw_ostream &OS) const {
183 SmallVector<unsigned, 4> Modes;
184 Modes.reserve(Map.size());
185
186 for (const auto &I : *this)
187 Modes.push_back(I.first);
188 if (Modes.empty()) {
189 OS << "{}";
190 return;
191 }
192 array_pod_sort(Modes.begin(), Modes.end());
193
194 OS << '{';
195 for (unsigned M : Modes) {
196 OS << ' ' << getModeName(M) << ':';
197 writeToStream(get(M), OS);
198 }
199 OS << " }";
200}
201
202void TypeSetByHwMode::writeToStream(const SetType &S, raw_ostream &OS) {
203 SmallVector<MVT, 4> Types(S.begin(), S.end());
204 array_pod_sort(Types.begin(), Types.end());
205
206 OS << '[';
207 for (unsigned i = 0, e = Types.size(); i != e; ++i) {
208 OS << ValueTypeByHwMode::getMVTName(Types[i]);
209 if (i != e-1)
210 OS << ' ';
211 }
212 OS << ']';
213}

215bool TypeSetByHwMode::operator==(const TypeSetByHwMode &VTS) const {
216 // The isSimple call is much quicker than hasDefault - check this first.
217 bool IsSimple = isSimple();
218 bool VTSIsSimple = VTS.isSimple();
219 if (IsSimple && VTSIsSimple)
220 return *begin() == *VTS.begin();
221
222 // Speedup: We have a default if the set is simple.
223 bool HaveDefault = IsSimple || hasDefault();
224 bool VTSHaveDefault = VTSIsSimple || VTS.hasDefault();
225 if (HaveDefault != VTSHaveDefault)
226 return false;
227
228 SmallDenseSet<unsigned, 4> Modes;
229 for (auto &I : *this)
230 Modes.insert(I.first);
231 for (const auto &I : VTS)
232 Modes.insert(I.first);
233
234 if (HaveDefault) {
235 // Both sets have default mode.
236 for (unsigned M : Modes) {
237 if (get(M) != VTS.get(M))
238 return false;
239 }
240 } else {
241 // Neither set has default mode.
242 for (unsigned M : Modes) {
243 // If there is no default mode, an empty set is equivalent to not having
244 // the corresponding mode.
245 bool NoModeThis = !hasMode(M) || get(M).empty();
246 bool NoModeVTS = !VTS.hasMode(M) || VTS.get(M).empty();
247 if (NoModeThis != NoModeVTS)
248 return false;
249 if (!NoModeThis)
250 if (get(M) != VTS.get(M))
251 return false;
252 }
253 }
254
255 return true;
256}

260 T.writeToStream(OS);
261 return OS;
262 }

270bool TypeSetByHwMode::intersect(SetType &Out, const SetType &In) {
271 bool OutP = Out.count(MVT::iPTR), InP = In.count(MVT::iPTR);
272 auto Int = [&In](MVT T) -> bool { return !In.count(T); };
273
274 if (OutP == InP)
275 return berase_if(Out, Int);
276
277 // Compute the intersection of scalars separately to account for only
278 // one set containing iPTR.
279 // The itersection of iPTR with a set of integer scalar types that does not
280 // include iPTR will result in the most specific scalar type:
281 // - iPTR is more specific than any set with two elements or more
282 // - iPTR is less specific than any single integer scalar type.
283 // For example
284 // { iPTR } * { i32 } -> { i32 }
285 // { iPTR } * { i32 i64 } -> { iPTR }
286 // and
287 // { iPTR i32 } * { i32 } -> { i32 }
288 // { iPTR i32 } * { i32 i64 } -> { i32 i64 }
289 // { iPTR i32 } * { i32 i64 i128 } -> { iPTR i32 }
290
291 // Compute the difference between the two sets in such a way that the
292 // iPTR is in the set that is being subtracted. This is to see if there
293 // are any extra scalars in the set without iPTR that are not in the
294 // set containing iPTR. Then the iPTR could be considered a "wildcard"
295 // matching these scalars. If there is only one such scalar, it would
296 // replace the iPTR, if there are more, the iPTR would be retained.
297 SetType Diff;
298 if (InP) {
299 Diff = Out;
300 berase_if(Diff, [&In](MVT T) { return In.count(T); });
301 // Pre-remove these elements and rely only on InP/OutP to determine
302 // whether a change has been made.
303 berase_if(Out, [&Diff](MVT T) { return Diff.count(T); });
304 } else {
305 Diff = In;
306 berase_if(Diff, [&Out](MVT T) { return Out.count(T); });
307 Out.erase(MVT::iPTR);
308 }
309
310 // The actual intersection.
311 bool Changed = berase_if(Out, Int);
312 unsigned NumD = Diff.size();
313 if (NumD == 0)
314 return Changed;
315
316 if (NumD == 1) {
317 Out.insert(*Diff.begin());
318 // This is a change only if Out was the one with iPTR (which is now
319 // being replaced).
320 Changed |= OutP;
321 } else {
322 // Multiple elements from Out are now replaced with iPTR.
323 Out.insert(MVT::iPTR);
324 Changed |= !OutP;
325 }
326 return Changed;
327}

329bool TypeSetByHwMode::validate() const {
330#ifndef NDEBUG
331 if (empty())
332 return true;
333 bool AllEmpty = true;
334 for (const auto &I : *this)
335 AllEmpty &= I.second.empty();
336 return !AllEmpty;
337#endif
338 return true;
339}

343bool TypeInfer::MergeInTypeInfo(TypeSetByHwMode &Out,
344 const TypeSetByHwMode &In) {
345 ValidateOnExit _1(Out, *this);
346 In.validate();
347 if (In.empty() || Out == In || TP.hasError())
348 return false;
349 if (Out.empty()) {
350 Out = In;
351 return true;
352 }
353
354 bool Changed = Out.constrain(In);
355 if (Changed && Out.empty())
356 TP.error("Type contradiction");
357
358 return Changed;
359}
360
361bool TypeInfer::forceArbitrary(TypeSetByHwMode &Out) {
362 ValidateOnExit _1(Out, *this);
363 if (TP.hasError())
364 return false;
365 assert(!Out.empty() && "cannot pick from an empty set");
366
367 bool Changed = false;
368 for (auto &I : Out) {
369 TypeSetByHwMode::SetType &S = I.second;
370 if (S.size() <= 1)
371 continue;
372 MVT T = *S.begin(); // Pick the first element.
373 S.clear();
374 S.insert(T);
375 Changed = true;
376 }
377 return Changed;
378}

420bool TypeInfer::EnforceAny(TypeSetByHwMode &Out) {
421 ValidateOnExit _1(Out, *this);

429template <typename Iter, typename Pred, typename Less>
430static Iter min_if(Iter B, Iter E, Pred P, Less L) {
431 if (B == E)
432 return E;
433 Iter Min = E;
434 for (Iter I = B; I != E; ++I) {
435 if (!P(*I))
436 continue;
437 if (Min == E || L(*I, *Min))
438 Min = I;
439 }
440 return Min;
441}
442
443template <typename Iter, typename Pred, typename Less>
444static Iter max_if(Iter B, Iter E, Pred P, Less L) {
445 if (B == E)
446 return E;
447 Iter Max = E;
448 for (Iter I = B; I != E; ++I) {
449 if (!P(*I))
450 continue;
451 if (Max == E || L(*Max, *I))
452 Max = I;
453 }
454 return Max;
455}

457/// Make sure that for each type in Small, there exists a larger type in Big.
458bool TypeInfer::EnforceSmallerThan(TypeSetByHwMode &Small,
459 TypeSetByHwMode &Big) {
460 ValidateOnExit _1(Small, *this), _2(Big, *this);
461 if (TP.hasError())
462 return false;
463 bool Changed = false;
464
465 if (Small.empty())
466 Changed |= EnforceAny(Small);
467 if (Big.empty())
468 Changed |= EnforceAny(Big);
469
470 assert(Small.hasDefault() && Big.hasDefault());
471
472 std::vector<unsigned> Modes = union_modes(Small, Big);
473
474 // 1. Only allow integer or floating point types and make sure that
475 // both sides are both integer or both floating point.
476 // 2. Make sure that either both sides have vector types, or neither
477 // of them does.
478 for (unsigned M : Modes) {
479 TypeSetByHwMode::SetType &S = Small.get(M);
480 TypeSetByHwMode::SetType &B = Big.get(M);
481
482 if (any_of(S, isIntegerOrPtr) && any_of(S, isIntegerOrPtr)) {
483 auto NotInt = [](MVT VT) { return !isIntegerOrPtr(VT); };
484 Changed |= berase_if(S, NotInt) |
485 berase_if(B, NotInt);
486 } else if (any_of(S, isFloatingPoint) && any_of(B, isFloatingPoint)) {
487 auto NotFP = [](MVT VT) { return !isFloatingPoint(VT); };
488 Changed |= berase_if(S, NotFP) |
489 berase_if(B, NotFP);
490 } else if (S.empty() || B.empty()) {
491 Changed = !S.empty() || !B.empty();
492 S.clear();
493 B.clear();
494 } else {
495 TP.error("Incompatible types");
496 return Changed;
497 }
498
499 if (none_of(S, isVector) || none_of(B, isVector)) {
500 Changed |= berase_if(S, isVector) |
501 berase_if(B, isVector);
502 }
503 }
504
505 auto LT = [](MVT A, MVT B) -> bool {
506 return A.getScalarSizeInBits() < B.getScalarSizeInBits() ||
507 (A.getScalarSizeInBits() == B.getScalarSizeInBits() &&
508 A.getSizeInBits() < B.getSizeInBits());
509 };
510 auto LE = [&LT](MVT A, MVT B) -> bool {
511 // This function is used when removing elements: when a vector is compared
512 // to a non-vector, it should return false (to avoid removal).
513 if (A.isVector() != B.isVector())
514 return false;
515
516 return LT(A, B) || (A.getScalarSizeInBits() == B.getScalarSizeInBits() &&
517 A.getSizeInBits() == B.getSizeInBits());
518 };
519
520 for (unsigned M : Modes) {
521 TypeSetByHwMode::SetType &S = Small.get(M);
522 TypeSetByHwMode::SetType &B = Big.get(M);
523 // MinS = min scalar in Small, remove all scalars from Big that are
524 // smaller-or-equal than MinS.
525 auto MinS = min_if(S.begin(), S.end(), isScalar, LT);
526 if (MinS != S.end())
527 Changed |= berase_if(B, std::bind(LE, std::placeholders::_1, *MinS));
528
529 // MaxS = max scalar in Big, remove all scalars from Small that are
530 // larger than MaxS.
531 auto MaxS = max_if(B.begin(), B.end(), isScalar, LT);
532 if (MaxS != B.end())
533 Changed |= berase_if(S, std::bind(LE, *MaxS, std::placeholders::_1));
534
535 // MinV = min vector in Small, remove all vectors from Big that are
536 // smaller-or-equal than MinV.
537 auto MinV = min_if(S.begin(), S.end(), isVector, LT);
538 if (MinV != S.end())
539 Changed |= berase_if(B, std::bind(LE, std::placeholders::_1, *MinV));
540
541 // MaxV = max vector in Big, remove all vectors from Small that are
542 // larger than MaxV.
543 auto MaxV = max_if(B.begin(), B.end(), isVector, LT);
544 if (MaxV != B.end())
545 Changed |= berase_if(S, std::bind(LE, *MaxV, std::placeholders::_1));
546 }
547
548 return Changed;
549}

551/// 1. Ensure that for each type T in Vec, T is a vector type, and that
552/// for each type U in Elem, U is a scalar type.
553/// 2. Ensure that for each (scalar) type U in Elem, there exists a (vector)
554/// type T in Vec, such that U is the element type of T.
555bool TypeInfer::EnforceVectorEltTypeIs(TypeSetByHwMode &Vec,
556 TypeSetByHwMode &Elem) {
557 ValidateOnExit _1(Vec, *this), _2(Elem, *this);
558 if (TP.hasError())
559 return false;
560 bool Changed = false;
561
562 if (Vec.empty())
563 Changed |= EnforceVector(Vec);
564 if (Elem.empty())
565 Changed |= EnforceScalar(Elem);
566
567 for (unsigned M : union_modes(Vec, Elem)) {
568 TypeSetByHwMode::SetType &V = Vec.get(M);
569 TypeSetByHwMode::SetType &E = Elem.get(M);
570
571 Changed |= berase_if(V, isScalar); // Scalar = !vector
572 Changed |= berase_if(E, isVector); // Vector = !scalar
573 assert(!V.empty() && !E.empty());
574
575 SmallSet<MVT,4> VT, ST;
576 // Collect element types from the "vector" set.
577 for (MVT T : V)
578 VT.insert(T.getVectorElementType());
579 // Collect scalar types from the "element" set.
580 for (MVT T : E)
581 ST.insert(T);
582
583 // Remove from V all (vector) types whose element type is not in S.
584 Changed |= berase_if(V, [&ST](MVT T) -> bool {
585 return !ST.count(T.getVectorElementType());
586 });
587 // Remove from E all (scalar) types, for which there is no corresponding
588 // type in V.
589 Changed |= berase_if(E, [&VT](MVT T) -> bool { return !VT.count(T); });
590 }
591
592 return Changed;
593}
594
595bool TypeInfer::EnforceVectorEltTypeIs(TypeSetByHwMode &Vec,
596 const ValueTypeByHwMode &VVT) {
597 TypeSetByHwMode Tmp(VVT);
598 ValidateOnExit _1(Vec, *this), _2(Tmp, *this);
599 return EnforceVectorEltTypeIs(Vec, Tmp);
600}

602/// Ensure that for each type T in Sub, T is a vector type, and there
603/// exists a type U in Vec such that U is a vector type with the same
604/// element type as T and at least as many elements as T.
605bool TypeInfer::EnforceVectorSubVectorTypeIs(TypeSetByHwMode &Vec,
606 TypeSetByHwMode &Sub) {
607 ValidateOnExit _1(Vec, *this), _2(Sub, *this);
608 if (TP.hasError())
609 return false;
610
611 /// Return true if B is a suB-vector of P, i.e. P is a suPer-vector of B.
612 auto IsSubVec = [](MVT B, MVT P) -> bool {
613 if (!B.isVector() || !P.isVector())
614 return false;
615 // Logically a <4 x i32> is a valid subvector of <n x 4 x i32>
616 // but until there are obvious use-cases for this, keep the
617 // types separate.
618 if (B.isScalableVector() != P.isScalableVector())
619 return false;
620 if (B.getVectorElementType() != P.getVectorElementType())
621 return false;
622 return B.getVectorNumElements() < P.getVectorNumElements();
623 };
624
625 /// Return true if S has no element (vector type) that T is a sub-vector of,
626 /// i.e. has the same element type as T and more elements.
627 auto NoSubV = [&IsSubVec](const TypeSetByHwMode::SetType &S, MVT T) -> bool {
628 for (const auto &I : S)
629 if (IsSubVec(T, I))
630 return false;
631 return true;
632 };
633
634 /// Return true if S has no element (vector type) that T is a super-vector
635 /// of, i.e. has the same element type as T and fewer elements.
636 auto NoSupV = [&IsSubVec](const TypeSetByHwMode::SetType &S, MVT T) -> bool {
637 for (const auto &I : S)
638 if (IsSubVec(I, T))
639 return false;
640 return true;
641 };
642
643 bool Changed = false;
644
645 if (Vec.empty())
646 Changed |= EnforceVector(Vec);
647 if (Sub.empty())
648 Changed |= EnforceVector(Sub);
649
650 for (unsigned M : union_modes(Vec, Sub)) {
651 TypeSetByHwMode::SetType &S = Sub.get(M);
652 TypeSetByHwMode::SetType &V = Vec.get(M);
653
654 Changed |= berase_if(S, isScalar);
655
656 // Erase all types from S that are not sub-vectors of a type in V.
657 Changed |= berase_if(S, std::bind(NoSubV, V, std::placeholders::_1));
658
659 // Erase all types from V that are not super-vectors of a type in S.
660 Changed |= berase_if(V, std::bind(NoSupV, S, std::placeholders::_1));
661 }
662
663 return Changed;
664}

666/// 1. Ensure that V has a scalar type iff W has a scalar type.
667/// 2. Ensure that for each vector type T in V, there exists a vector
668/// type U in W, such that T and U have the same number of elements.
669/// 3. Ensure that for each vector type U in W, there exists a vector
670/// type T in V, such that T and U have the same number of elements
671/// (reverse of 2).
672bool TypeInfer::EnforceSameNumElts(TypeSetByHwMode &V, TypeSetByHwMode &W) {
673 ValidateOnExit _1(V, *this), _2(W, *this);
674 if (TP.hasError())
675 return false;
676
677 bool Changed = false;
678 if (V.empty())
679 Changed |= EnforceAny(V);
680 if (W.empty())
681 Changed |= EnforceAny(W);
682
683 // An actual vector type cannot have 0 elements, so we can treat scalars
684 // as zero-length vectors. This way both vectors and scalars can be
685 // processed identically.
686 auto NoLength = [](const SmallSet<unsigned,2> &Lengths, MVT T) -> bool {
687 return !Lengths.count(T.isVector() ? T.getVectorNumElements() : 0);
688 };
689
690 for (unsigned M : union_modes(V, W)) {
691 TypeSetByHwMode::SetType &VS = V.get(M);
692 TypeSetByHwMode::SetType &WS = W.get(M);
693
694 SmallSet<unsigned,2> VN, WN;
695 for (MVT T : VS)
696 VN.insert(T.isVector() ? T.getVectorNumElements() : 0);
697 for (MVT T : WS)
698 WN.insert(T.isVector() ? T.getVectorNumElements() : 0);
699
700 Changed |= berase_if(VS, std::bind(NoLength, WN, std::placeholders::_1));
701 Changed |= berase_if(WS, std::bind(NoLength, VN, std::placeholders::_1));
702 }
703 return Changed;
704}
705
706/// 1. Ensure that for each type T in A, there exists a type U in B,
707/// such that T and U have equal size in bits.
708/// 2. Ensure that for each type U in B, there exists a type T in A
709/// such that T and U have equal size in bits (reverse of 1).
710bool TypeInfer::EnforceSameSize(TypeSetByHwMode &A, TypeSetByHwMode &B) {
711 ValidateOnExit _1(A, *this), _2(B, *this);
712 if (TP.hasError())
713 return false;
714 bool Changed = false;
715 if (A.empty())
716 Changed |= EnforceAny(A);
717 if (B.empty())
718 Changed |= EnforceAny(B);
719
720 auto NoSize = [](const SmallSet<unsigned,2> &Sizes, MVT T) -> bool {
721 return !Sizes.count(T.getSizeInBits());
722 };
723
724 for (unsigned M : union_modes(A, B)) {
725 TypeSetByHwMode::SetType &AS = A.get(M);
726 TypeSetByHwMode::SetType &BS = B.get(M);
727 SmallSet<unsigned,2> AN, BN;
728
729 for (MVT T : AS)
730 AN.insert(T.getSizeInBits());
731 for (MVT T : BS)
732 BN.insert(T.getSizeInBits());
733
734 Changed |= berase_if(AS, std::bind(NoSize, BN, std::placeholders::_1));
735 Changed |= berase_if(BS, std::bind(NoSize, AN, std::placeholders::_1));
736 }
737
738 return Changed;
739}
740
741void TypeInfer::expandOverloads(TypeSetByHwMode &VTS) {
742 ValidateOnExit _1(VTS, *this);
743 const TypeSetByHwMode &Legal = getLegalTypes();
744 assert(Legal.isDefaultOnly() && "Default-mode only expected");
745 const TypeSetByHwMode::SetType &LegalTypes = Legal.get(DefaultMode);
746
747 for (auto &I : VTS)
748 expandOverloads(I.second, LegalTypes);
749}
750
751void TypeInfer::expandOverloads(TypeSetByHwMode::SetType &Out,
752 const TypeSetByHwMode::SetType &Legal) {
753 std::set<MVT> Ovs;
754 for (MVT T : Out) {
755 if (!T.isOverloaded())
756 continue;
757
758 Ovs.insert(T);
759 // MachineValueTypeSet allows iteration and erasing.
760 Out.erase(T);
761 }
762
763 for (MVT Ov : Ovs) {
764 switch (Ov.SimpleTy) {
765 case MVT::iPTRAny:
766 Out.insert(MVT::iPTR);
767 return;
768 case MVT::iFATPTRAny:
769 Out.insert(MVT::iFATPTR64);
770 Out.insert(MVT::iFATPTR128);
771 Out.insert(MVT::iFATPTR256);
772 Out.insert(MVT::iFATPTR512);
773 return;
774 case MVT::iAny:
775 for (MVT T : MVT::integer_valuetypes())
776 if (Legal.count(T))
777 Out.insert(T);
778 for (MVT T : MVT::integer_vector_valuetypes())
779 if (Legal.count(T))
780 Out.insert(T);
781 return;
782 case MVT::fAny:
783 for (MVT T : MVT::fp_valuetypes())
784 if (Legal.count(T))
785 Out.insert(T);
786 for (MVT T : MVT::fp_vector_valuetypes())
787 if (Legal.count(T))
788 Out.insert(T);
789 return;
790 case MVT::vAny:
791 for (MVT T : MVT::vector_valuetypes())
792 if (Legal.count(T))
793 Out.insert(T);
794 return;
795 case MVT::Any:
796 for (MVT T : MVT::all_valuetypes())
797 if (Legal.count(T))
798 Out.insert(T);
799 return;
800 default:
801 break;
802 }
803 }
804}
805
806const TypeSetByHwMode &TypeInfer::getLegalTypes() {
807 if (!LegalTypesCached) {
808 TypeSetByHwMode::SetType &LegalTypes = LegalCache.getOrCreate(DefaultMode);
809 // Stuff all types from all modes into the default mode.
810 const TypeSetByHwMode &LTS = TP.getDAGPatterns().getLegalTypes();
811 for (const auto &I : LTS)
812 LegalTypes.insert(I.second);
813 LegalTypesCached = true;
814 }
815 assert(LegalCache.isDefaultOnly() && "Default-mode only expected");
816 return LegalCache;
817}

857bool TreePredicateFn::hasPredCode() const {
858 return isLoad() || isStore() || isAtomic() ||
859 !PatFragRec->getRecord()->getValueAsString("PredicateCode").empty();
860}
861
862std::string TreePredicateFn::getPredCode() const {
863 std::string Code = "";
864
865 if (!isLoad() && !isStore() && !isAtomic()) {
866 Record *MemoryVT = getMemoryVT();
867
868 if (MemoryVT)
869 PrintFatalError(getOrigPatFragRecord()->getRecord()->getLoc(),
870 "MemoryVT requires IsLoad or IsStore");
871 }
872
873 if (!isLoad() && !isStore()) {
874 if (isUnindexed())
875 PrintFatalError(getOrigPatFragRecord()->getRecord()->getLoc(),
876 "IsUnindexed requires IsLoad or IsStore");
877
878 Record *ScalarMemoryVT = getScalarMemoryVT();
879
880 if (ScalarMemoryVT)
881 PrintFatalError(getOrigPatFragRecord()->getRecord()->getLoc(),
882 "ScalarMemoryVT requires IsLoad or IsStore");
883 }
884
885 if (isLoad() + isStore() + isAtomic() > 1)
886 PrintFatalError(getOrigPatFragRecord()->getRecord()->getLoc(),
887 "IsLoad, IsStore, and IsAtomic are mutually exclusive");
888
889 if (isLoad()) {
890 if (!isUnindexed() && !isNonExtLoad() && !isAnyExtLoad() &&
891 !isSignExtLoad() && !isZeroExtLoad() && getMemoryVT() == nullptr &&
892 getScalarMemoryVT() == nullptr)
893 PrintFatalError(getOrigPatFragRecord()->getRecord()->getLoc(),
894 "IsLoad cannot be used by itself");
895 } else {
896 if (isNonExtLoad())
897 PrintFatalError(getOrigPatFragRecord()->getRecord()->getLoc(),
898 "IsNonExtLoad requires IsLoad");
899 if (isAnyExtLoad())
900 PrintFatalError(getOrigPatFragRecord()->getRecord()->getLoc(),
901 "IsAnyExtLoad requires IsLoad");
902 if (isSignExtLoad())
903 PrintFatalError(getOrigPatFragRecord()->getRecord()->getLoc(),
904 "IsSignExtLoad requires IsLoad");
905 if (isZeroExtLoad())
906 PrintFatalError(getOrigPatFragRecord()->getRecord()->getLoc(),
907 "IsZeroExtLoad requires IsLoad");
908 }
909
910 if (isStore()) {
911 if (!isUnindexed() && !isTruncStore() && !isNonTruncStore() &&
912 getMemoryVT() == nullptr && getScalarMemoryVT() == nullptr)
913 PrintFatalError(getOrigPatFragRecord()->getRecord()->getLoc(),
914 "IsStore cannot be used by itself");
915 } else {
916 if (isNonTruncStore())
917 PrintFatalError(getOrigPatFragRecord()->getRecord()->getLoc(),
918 "IsNonTruncStore requires IsStore");
919 if (isTruncStore())
920 PrintFatalError(getOrigPatFragRecord()->getRecord()->getLoc(),
921 "IsTruncStore requires IsStore");
922 }
923
924 if (isAtomic()) {
925 if (getMemoryVT() == nullptr && !isAtomicOrderingMonotonic() &&
926 !isAtomicOrderingAcquire() && !isAtomicOrderingRelease() &&
927 !isAtomicOrderingAcquireRelease() &&
928 !isAtomicOrderingSequentiallyConsistent() &&
929 !isAtomicOrderingAcquireOrStronger() &&
930 !isAtomicOrderingReleaseOrStronger() &&
931 !isAtomicOrderingWeakerThanAcquire() &&
932 !isAtomicOrderingWeakerThanRelease())
933 PrintFatalError(getOrigPatFragRecord()->getRecord()->getLoc(),
934 "IsAtomic cannot be used by itself");
935 } else {
936 if (isAtomicOrderingMonotonic())
937 PrintFatalError(getOrigPatFragRecord()->getRecord()->getLoc(),
938 "IsAtomicOrderingMonotonic requires IsAtomic");
939 if (isAtomicOrderingAcquire())
940 PrintFatalError(getOrigPatFragRecord()->getRecord()->getLoc(),
941 "IsAtomicOrderingAcquire requires IsAtomic");
942 if (isAtomicOrderingRelease())
943 PrintFatalError(getOrigPatFragRecord()->getRecord()->getLoc(),
944 "IsAtomicOrderingRelease requires IsAtomic");
945 if (isAtomicOrderingAcquireRelease())
946 PrintFatalError(getOrigPatFragRecord()->getRecord()->getLoc(),
947 "IsAtomicOrderingAcquireRelease requires IsAtomic");
948 if (isAtomicOrderingSequentiallyConsistent())
949 PrintFatalError(getOrigPatFragRecord()->getRecord()->getLoc(),
950 "IsAtomicOrderingSequentiallyConsistent requires IsAtomic");
951 if (isAtomicOrderingAcquireOrStronger())
952 PrintFatalError(getOrigPatFragRecord()->getRecord()->getLoc(),
953 "IsAtomicOrderingAcquireOrStronger requires IsAtomic");
954 if (isAtomicOrderingReleaseOrStronger())
955 PrintFatalError(getOrigPatFragRecord()->getRecord()->getLoc(),
956 "IsAtomicOrderingReleaseOrStronger requires IsAtomic");
957 if (isAtomicOrderingWeakerThanAcquire())
958 PrintFatalError(getOrigPatFragRecord()->getRecord()->getLoc(),
959 "IsAtomicOrderingWeakerThanAcquire requires IsAtomic");
960 }
961
962 if (isLoad() || isStore() || isAtomic()) {
963 StringRef SDNodeName =
964 isLoad() ? "LoadSDNode" : isStore() ? "StoreSDNode" : "AtomicSDNode";
965
966 Record *MemoryVT = getMemoryVT();
967
968 if (MemoryVT)
969 Code += ("if (cast<" + SDNodeName + ">(N)->getMemoryVT() != MVT::" +
970 MemoryVT->getName() + ") return false;\n")
971 .str();
972 }
973
974 if (isAtomic() && isAtomicOrderingMonotonic())
975 Code += "if (cast<AtomicSDNode>(N)->getOrdering() != "
976 "AtomicOrdering::Monotonic) return false;\n";
977 if (isAtomic() && isAtomicOrderingAcquire())
978 Code += "if (cast<AtomicSDNode>(N)->getOrdering() != "
979 "AtomicOrdering::Acquire) return false;\n";
980 if (isAtomic() && isAtomicOrderingRelease())
981 Code += "if (cast<AtomicSDNode>(N)->getOrdering() != "
982 "AtomicOrdering::Release) return false;\n";
983 if (isAtomic() && isAtomicOrderingAcquireRelease())
984 Code += "if (cast<AtomicSDNode>(N)->getOrdering() != "
985 "AtomicOrdering::AcquireRelease) return false;\n";
986 if (isAtomic() && isAtomicOrderingSequentiallyConsistent())
987 Code += "if (cast<AtomicSDNode>(N)->getOrdering() != "
988 "AtomicOrdering::SequentiallyConsistent) return false;\n";
989
990 if (isAtomic() && isAtomicOrderingAcquireOrStronger())
991 Code += "if (!isAcquireOrStronger(cast<AtomicSDNode>(N)->getOrdering())) "
992 "return false;\n";
993 if (isAtomic() && isAtomicOrderingWeakerThanAcquire())
994 Code += "if (isAcquireOrStronger(cast<AtomicSDNode>(N)->getOrdering())) "
995 "return false;\n";
996
997 if (isAtomic() && isAtomicOrderingReleaseOrStronger())
998 Code += "if (!isReleaseOrStronger(cast<AtomicSDNode>(N)->getOrdering())) "
999 "return false;\n";
1000 if (isAtomic() && isAtomicOrderingWeakerThanRelease())
1001 Code += "if (isReleaseOrStronger(cast<AtomicSDNode>(N)->getOrdering())) "
1002 "return false;\n";
1003
1004 if (isLoad() || isStore()) {
1005 StringRef SDNodeName = isLoad() ? "LoadSDNode" : "StoreSDNode";
1006
1007 if (isUnindexed())
1008 Code += ("if (cast<" + SDNodeName +
1009 ">(N)->getAddressingMode() != ISD::UNINDEXED) "
1010 "return false;\n")
1011 .str();
1012
1013 if (isLoad()) {
1014 if ((isNonExtLoad() + isAnyExtLoad() + isSignExtLoad() +
1015 isZeroExtLoad()) > 1)
1016 PrintFatalError(getOrigPatFragRecord()->getRecord()->getLoc(),
1017 "IsNonExtLoad, IsAnyExtLoad, IsSignExtLoad, and "
1018 "IsZeroExtLoad are mutually exclusive");
1019 if (isNonExtLoad())
1020 Code += "if (cast<LoadSDNode>(N)->getExtensionType() != "
1021 "ISD::NON_EXTLOAD) return false;\n";
1022 if (isAnyExtLoad())
1023 Code += "if (cast<LoadSDNode>(N)->getExtensionType() != ISD::EXTLOAD) "
1024 "return false;\n";
1025 if (isSignExtLoad())
1026 Code += "if (cast<LoadSDNode>(N)->getExtensionType() != ISD::SEXTLOAD) "
1027 "return false;\n";
1028 if (isZeroExtLoad())
1029 Code += "if (cast<LoadSDNode>(N)->getExtensionType() != ISD::ZEXTLOAD) "
1030 "return false;\n";
1031 } else {
1032 if ((isNonTruncStore() + isTruncStore()) > 1)
1033 PrintFatalError(
1034 getOrigPatFragRecord()->getRecord()->getLoc(),
1035 "IsNonTruncStore, and IsTruncStore are mutually exclusive");
1036 if (isNonTruncStore())
1037 Code +=
1038 " if (cast<StoreSDNode>(N)->isTruncatingStore()) return false;\n";
1039 if (isTruncStore())
1040 Code +=
1041 " if (!cast<StoreSDNode>(N)->isTruncatingStore()) return false;\n";
1042 }
1043
1044 Record *ScalarMemoryVT = getScalarMemoryVT();
1045
1046 if (ScalarMemoryVT)
1047 Code += ("if (cast<" + SDNodeName +
1048 ">(N)->getMemoryVT().getScalarType() != MVT::" +
1049 ScalarMemoryVT->getName() + ") return false;\n")
1050 .str();
1051 }
1052
1053 std::string PredicateCode = PatFragRec->getRecord()->getValueAsString("PredicateCode");
1054
1055 Code += PredicateCode;
1056
1057 if (PredicateCode.empty() && !Code.empty())
1058 Code += "return true;\n";
1059
1060 return Code;
1061}

1200/// getCodeToRunOnSDNode - Return the code for the function body that
1201/// evaluates this predicate. The argument is expected to be in "Node",
1202/// not N. This handles casting and conversion to a concrete node type as
1203/// appropriate.
1204std::string TreePredicateFn::getCodeToRunOnSDNode() const {
1205 // Handle immediate predicates first.
1206 std::string ImmCode = getImmCode();
1207 if (!ImmCode.empty()) {
1208 if (isLoad())
1209 PrintFatalError(getOrigPatFragRecord()->getRecord()->getLoc(),
1210 "IsLoad cannot be used with ImmLeaf or its subclasses");
1211 if (isStore())
1212 PrintFatalError(getOrigPatFragRecord()->getRecord()->getLoc(),
1213 "IsStore cannot be used with ImmLeaf or its subclasses");
1214 if (isUnindexed())
1215 PrintFatalError(
1216 getOrigPatFragRecord()->getRecord()->getLoc(),
1217 "IsUnindexed cannot be used with ImmLeaf or its subclasses");
1218 if (isNonExtLoad())
1219 PrintFatalError(
1220 getOrigPatFragRecord()->getRecord()->getLoc(),
1221 "IsNonExtLoad cannot be used with ImmLeaf or its subclasses");
1222 if (isAnyExtLoad())
1223 PrintFatalError(
1224 getOrigPatFragRecord()->getRecord()->getLoc(),
1225 "IsAnyExtLoad cannot be used with ImmLeaf or its subclasses");
1226 if (isSignExtLoad())
1227 PrintFatalError(
1228 getOrigPatFragRecord()->getRecord()->getLoc(),
1229 "IsSignExtLoad cannot be used with ImmLeaf or its subclasses");
1230 if (isZeroExtLoad())
1231 PrintFatalError(
1232 getOrigPatFragRecord()->getRecord()->getLoc(),
1233 "IsZeroExtLoad cannot be used with ImmLeaf or its subclasses");
1234 if (isNonTruncStore())
1235 PrintFatalError(
1236 getOrigPatFragRecord()->getRecord()->getLoc(),
1237 "IsNonTruncStore cannot be used with ImmLeaf or its subclasses");
1238 if (isTruncStore())
1239 PrintFatalError(
1240 getOrigPatFragRecord()->getRecord()->getLoc(),
1241 "IsTruncStore cannot be used with ImmLeaf or its subclasses");
1242 if (getMemoryVT())
1243 PrintFatalError(getOrigPatFragRecord()->getRecord()->getLoc(),
1244 "MemoryVT cannot be used with ImmLeaf or its subclasses");
1245 if (getScalarMemoryVT())
1246 PrintFatalError(
1247 getOrigPatFragRecord()->getRecord()->getLoc(),
1248 "ScalarMemoryVT cannot be used with ImmLeaf or its subclasses");
1249
1250 std::string Result = (" " + getImmType() + " Imm = ").str();
1251 if (immCodeUsesAPFloat())
1252 Result += "cast<ConstantFPSDNode>(Node)->getValueAPF();\n";
1253 else if (immCodeUsesAPInt())
1254 Result += "cast<ConstantSDNode>(Node)->getAPIntValue();\n";
1255 else
1256 Result += "cast<ConstantSDNode>(Node)->getSExtValue();\n";
1257 return Result + ImmCode;
1258 }
1259
1260 // Handle arbitrary node predicates.
1261 assert(hasPredCode() && "Don't have any predicate code!");
1262 StringRef ClassName;
1263 if (PatFragRec->getOnlyTree()->isLeaf())
1264 ClassName = "SDNode";
1265 else {
1266 Record *Op = PatFragRec->getOnlyTree()->getOperator();
1267 ClassName = PatFragRec->getDAGPatterns().getSDNodeInfo(Op).getSDClassName();
1268 }
1269 std::string Result;
1270 if (ClassName == "SDNode")
1271 Result = " SDNode *N = Node;\n";
1272 else
1273 Result = " auto *N = cast<" + ClassName.str() + ">(Node);\n";
1274
1275 return (Twine(Result) + " (void)N;\n" + getPredCode()).str();
1276}

1279// PatternToMatch implementation
1280//
1281
1282static bool isImmAllOnesAllZerosMatch(const TreePatternNode *P) {
1283 if (!P->isLeaf())
1284 return false;
1285 DefInit *DI = dyn_cast<DefInit>(P->getLeafValue());
1286 if (!DI)
1287 return false;
1288
1289 Record *R = DI->getDef();
1290 return R->getName() == "immAllOnesV" || R->getName() == "immAllZerosV";
1291}
1292
1293/// getPatternSize - Return the 'size' of this pattern. We want to match large
1294/// patterns before small ones. This is used to determine the size of a
1295/// pattern.
1296static unsigned getPatternSize(const TreePatternNode *P,
1297 const CodeGenDAGPatterns &CGP) {
1298 unsigned Size = 3; // The node itself.
1299 // If the root node is a ConstantSDNode, increases its size.
1300 // e.g. (set R32:$dst, 0).
1301 if (P->isLeaf() && isa<IntInit>(P->getLeafValue()))
1302 Size += 2;
1303
1304 if (const ComplexPattern *AM = P->getComplexPatternInfo(CGP)) {
1305 Size += AM->getComplexity();
1306 // We don't want to count any children twice, so return early.
1307 return Size;
1308 }
1309
1310 // If this node has some predicate function that must match, it adds to the
1311 // complexity of this node.
1312 if (!P->getPredicateCalls().empty())
1313 ++Size;
1314
1315 // Count children in the count if they are also nodes.
1316 for (unsigned i = 0, e = P->getNumChildren(); i != e; ++i) {
1317 const TreePatternNode *Child = P->getChild(i);
1318 if (!Child->isLeaf() && Child->getNumTypes()) {
1319 const TypeSetByHwMode &T0 = Child->getExtType(0);
1320 // At this point, all variable type sets should be simple, i.e. only
1321 // have a default mode.
1322 if (T0.getMachineValueType() != MVT::Other) {
1323 Size += getPatternSize(Child, CGP);
1324 continue;
1325 }
1326 }
1327 if (Child->isLeaf()) {
1328 if (isa<IntInit>(Child->getLeafValue()))
1329 Size += 5; // Matches a ConstantSDNode (+3) and a specific value (+2).
1330 else if (Child->getComplexPatternInfo(CGP))
1331 Size += getPatternSize(Child, CGP);
1332 else if (isImmAllOnesAllZerosMatch(Child))
1333 Size += 4; // Matches a build_vector(+3) and a predicate (+1).
1334 else if (!Child->getPredicateCalls().empty())
1335 ++Size;
1336 }
1337 }
1338
1339 return Size;
1340}
1341
1342/// Compute the complexity metric for the input pattern. This roughly
1343/// corresponds to the number of nodes that are covered.
1344int PatternToMatch::
1345getPatternComplexity(const CodeGenDAGPatterns &CGP) const {
1346 return getPatternSize(getSrcPattern(), CGP) + getAddedComplexity();
1347}
1348
1349/// getPredicateCheck - Return a single string containing all of this
1350/// pattern's predicates concatenated with "&&" operators.
1351///
1352std::string PatternToMatch::getPredicateCheck() const {
1353 SmallVector<const Predicate*,4> PredList;
1354 for (const Predicate &P : Predicates)
1355 PredList.push_back(&P);
1356 llvm::sort(PredList, deref<llvm::less>());
1357
1358 std::string Check;
1359 for (unsigned i = 0, e = PredList.size(); i != e; ++i) {
1360 if (i != 0)
1361 Check += " && ";
1362 Check += '(' + PredList[i]->getCondString() + ')';
1363 }
1364 return Check;
1365}

1367//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
1368// SDTypeConstraint implementation
1369//
1370
1371SDTypeConstraint::SDTypeConstraint(Record *R, const CodeGenHwModes &CGH) {
1372 OperandNo = R->getValueAsInt("OperandNum");
1373
1374 if (R->isSubClassOf("SDTCisVT")) {
1375 ConstraintType = SDTCisVT;
1376 VVT = getValueTypeByHwMode(R->getValueAsDef("VT"), CGH);
1377 for (const auto &P : VVT)
1378 if (P.second == MVT::isVoid)
1379 PrintFatalError(R->getLoc(), "Cannot use 'Void' as type to SDTCisVT");
1380 } else if (R->isSubClassOf("SDTCisPtrTy")) {
1381 ConstraintType = SDTCisPtrTy;
1382 } else if (R->isSubClassOf("SDTCisInt")) {
1383 ConstraintType = SDTCisInt;
1384 } else if (R->isSubClassOf("SDTCisFP")) {
1385 ConstraintType = SDTCisFP;
1386 } else if (R->isSubClassOf("SDTCisVec")) {
1387 ConstraintType = SDTCisVec;
1388 } else if (R->isSubClassOf("SDTCisSameAs")) {
1389 ConstraintType = SDTCisSameAs;
1390 x.SDTCisSameAs_Info.OtherOperandNum = R->getValueAsInt("OtherOperandNum");
1391 } else if (R->isSubClassOf("SDTCisVTSmallerThanOp")) {
1392 ConstraintType = SDTCisVTSmallerThanOp;
1393 x.SDTCisVTSmallerThanOp_Info.OtherOperandNum =
1394 R->getValueAsInt("OtherOperandNum");
1395 } else if (R->isSubClassOf("SDTCisOpSmallerThanOp")) {
1396 ConstraintType = SDTCisOpSmallerThanOp;
1397 x.SDTCisOpSmallerThanOp_Info.BigOperandNum =
1398 R->getValueAsInt("BigOperandNum");
1399 } else if (R->isSubClassOf("SDTCisEltOfVec")) {
1400 ConstraintType = SDTCisEltOfVec;
1401 x.SDTCisEltOfVec_Info.OtherOperandNum = R->getValueAsInt("OtherOpNum");
1402 } else if (R->isSubClassOf("SDTCisSubVecOfVec")) {
1403 ConstraintType = SDTCisSubVecOfVec;
1404 x.SDTCisSubVecOfVec_Info.OtherOperandNum =
1405 R->getValueAsInt("OtherOpNum");
1406 } else if (R->isSubClassOf("SDTCVecEltisVT")) {
1407 ConstraintType = SDTCVecEltisVT;
1408 VVT = getValueTypeByHwMode(R->getValueAsDef("VT"), CGH);
1409 for (const auto &P : VVT) {
1410 MVT T = P.second;
1411 if (T.isVector())
1412 PrintFatalError(R->getLoc(),
1413 "Cannot use vector type as SDTCVecEltisVT");
1414 if (!T.isInteger() && !T.isFloatingPoint())
1415 PrintFatalError(R->getLoc(), "Must use integer or floating point type "
1416 "as SDTCVecEltisVT");
1417 }
1418 } else if (R->isSubClassOf("SDTCisSameNumEltsAs")) {
1419 ConstraintType = SDTCisSameNumEltsAs;
1420 x.SDTCisSameNumEltsAs_Info.OtherOperandNum =
1421 R->getValueAsInt("OtherOperandNum");
1422 } else if (R->isSubClassOf("SDTCisSameSizeAs")) {
1423 ConstraintType = SDTCisSameSizeAs;
1424 x.SDTCisSameSizeAs_Info.OtherOperandNum =
1425 R->getValueAsInt("OtherOperandNum");
1426 } else {
1427 PrintFatalError(R->getLoc(),
1428 "Unrecognized SDTypeConstraint '" + R->getName() + "'!\n");
1429 }
1430}
1431
1432/// getOperandNum - Return the node corresponding to operand #OpNo in tree
1433/// N, and the result number in ResNo.
1434static TreePatternNode *getOperandNum(unsigned OpNo, TreePatternNode *N,
1435 const SDNodeInfo &NodeInfo,
1436 unsigned &ResNo) {
1437 unsigned NumResults = NodeInfo.getNumResults();
1438 if (OpNo < NumResults) {
1439 ResNo = OpNo;
1440 return N;
1441 }
1442
1443 OpNo -= NumResults;
1444
1445 if (OpNo >= N->getNumChildren()) {
1446 std::string S;
1447 raw_string_ostream OS(S);
1448 OS << "Invalid operand number in type constraint "
1449 << (OpNo+NumResults) << " ";
1450 N->print(OS);
1451 PrintFatalError(OS.str());
1452 }
1453
1454 return N->getChild(OpNo);
1455}
1456
1457/// ApplyTypeConstraint - Given a node in a pattern, apply this type
1458/// constraint to the nodes operands. This returns true if it makes a
1459/// change, false otherwise. If a type contradiction is found, flag an error.
1460bool SDTypeConstraint::ApplyTypeConstraint(TreePatternNode *N,
1461 const SDNodeInfo &NodeInfo,
1462 TreePattern &TP) const {
1463 if (TP.hasError())
1464 return false;
1465
1466 unsigned ResNo = 0; // The result number being referenced.
1467 TreePatternNode *NodeToApply = getOperandNum(OperandNo, N, NodeInfo, ResNo);
1468 TypeInfer &TI = TP.getInfer();
1469
1470 switch (ConstraintType) {
1471 case SDTCisVT:
1472 // Operand must be a particular type.
1473 return NodeToApply->UpdateNodeType(ResNo, VVT, TP);
1474 case SDTCisPtrTy: {
1475 // Operand must be a pointer type.
1476 // If we support fat pointers, then this narrows it down to two types.
1477 if (TP.getDAGPatterns().enableFatPointers()) {
1478 // FIXME: We should be able to do the type inference correctly from the
1479 // two types, but for now just disable this constraint on architectures
1480 // with fat pointers.
1481 return false;
1482 ArrayRef<ValueTypeByHwMode> PtrTys({ValueTypeByHwMode(MVT::iFATPTRAny),
1483 ValueTypeByHwMode(MVT::iPTR)});
1484 return NodeToApply->UpdateNodeType(ResNo, PtrTys, TP);
1485 }
1486 return NodeToApply->UpdateNodeType(ResNo, MVT::iPTR, TP);
1487 }
1488 case SDTCisInt:
1489 // Require it to be one of the legal integer VTs.
1490 return TI.EnforceInteger(NodeToApply->getExtType(ResNo));
1491 case SDTCisFP:
1492 // Require it to be one of the legal fp VTs.
1493 return TI.EnforceFloatingPoint(NodeToApply->getExtType(ResNo));
1494 case SDTCisVec:
1495 // Require it to be one of the legal vector VTs.
1496 return TI.EnforceVector(NodeToApply->getExtType(ResNo));
1497 case SDTCisSameAs: {
1498 unsigned OResNo = 0;
1499 TreePatternNode *OtherNode =
1500 getOperandNum(x.SDTCisSameAs_Info.OtherOperandNum, N, NodeInfo, OResNo);
1501 return NodeToApply->UpdateNodeType(ResNo, OtherNode->getExtType(OResNo),TP)|
1502 OtherNode->UpdateNodeType(OResNo,NodeToApply->getExtType(ResNo),TP);
1503 }
1504 case SDTCisVTSmallerThanOp: {
1505 // The NodeToApply must be a leaf node that is a VT. OtherOperandNum must
1506 // have an integer type that is smaller than the VT.
1507 if (!NodeToApply->isLeaf() ||
1508 !isa<DefInit>(NodeToApply->getLeafValue()) ||
1509 !static_cast<DefInit*>(NodeToApply->getLeafValue())->getDef()
1510 ->isSubClassOf("ValueType")) {
1511 TP.error(N->getOperator()->getName() + " expects a VT operand!");
1512 return false;
1513 }
1514 DefInit *DI = static_cast<DefInit*>(NodeToApply->getLeafValue());
1515 const CodeGenTarget &T = TP.getDAGPatterns().getTargetInfo();
1516 auto VVT = getValueTypeByHwMode(DI->getDef(), T.getHwModes());
1517 TypeSetByHwMode TypeListTmp(VVT);
1518
1519 unsigned OResNo = 0;
1520 TreePatternNode *OtherNode =
1521 getOperandNum(x.SDTCisVTSmallerThanOp_Info.OtherOperandNum, N, NodeInfo,
1522 OResNo);
1523
1524 return TI.EnforceSmallerThan(TypeListTmp, OtherNode->getExtType(OResNo));
1525 }
1526 case SDTCisOpSmallerThanOp: {
1527 unsigned BResNo = 0;
1528 TreePatternNode *BigOperand =
1529 getOperandNum(x.SDTCisOpSmallerThanOp_Info.BigOperandNum, N, NodeInfo,
1530 BResNo);
1531 return TI.EnforceSmallerThan(NodeToApply->getExtType(ResNo),
1532 BigOperand->getExtType(BResNo));
1533 }
1534 case SDTCisEltOfVec: {
1535 unsigned VResNo = 0;
1536 TreePatternNode *VecOperand =
1537 getOperandNum(x.SDTCisEltOfVec_Info.OtherOperandNum, N, NodeInfo,
1538 VResNo);
1539 // Filter vector types out of VecOperand that don't have the right element
1540 // type.
1541 return TI.EnforceVectorEltTypeIs(VecOperand->getExtType(VResNo),
1542 NodeToApply->getExtType(ResNo));
1543 }
1544 case SDTCisSubVecOfVec: {
1545 unsigned VResNo = 0;
1546 TreePatternNode *BigVecOperand =
1547 getOperandNum(x.SDTCisSubVecOfVec_Info.OtherOperandNum, N, NodeInfo,
1548 VResNo);
1549
1550 // Filter vector types out of BigVecOperand that don't have the
1551 // right subvector type.
1552 return TI.EnforceVectorSubVectorTypeIs(BigVecOperand->getExtType(VResNo),
1553 NodeToApply->getExtType(ResNo));
1554 }
1555 case SDTCVecEltisVT: {
1556 return TI.EnforceVectorEltTypeIs(NodeToApply->getExtType(ResNo), VVT);
1557 }
1558 case SDTCisSameNumEltsAs: {
1559 unsigned OResNo = 0;
1560 TreePatternNode *OtherNode =
1561 getOperandNum(x.SDTCisSameNumEltsAs_Info.OtherOperandNum,
1562 N, NodeInfo, OResNo);
1563 return TI.EnforceSameNumElts(OtherNode->getExtType(OResNo),
1564 NodeToApply->getExtType(ResNo));
1565 }
1566 case SDTCisSameSizeAs: {
1567 unsigned OResNo = 0;
1568 TreePatternNode *OtherNode =
1569 getOperandNum(x.SDTCisSameSizeAs_Info.OtherOperandNum,
1570 N, NodeInfo, OResNo);
1571 return TI.EnforceSameSize(OtherNode->getExtType(OResNo),
1572 NodeToApply->getExtType(ResNo));
1573 }
1574 }
1575 llvm_unreachable("Invalid ConstraintType!");
1576}
1577
1578// Update the node type to match an instruction operand or result as specified
1579// in the ins or outs lists on the instruction definition. Return true if the
1580// type was actually changed.
1581bool TreePatternNode::UpdateNodeTypeFromInst(unsigned ResNo,
1582 Record *Operand,
1583 TreePattern &TP) {
1584 // The 'unknown' operand indicates that types should be inferred from the
1585 // context.
1586 if (Operand->isSubClassOf("unknown_class"))
1587 return false;
1588
1589 // The Operand class specifies a type directly.
1590 if (Operand->isSubClassOf("Operand")) {
1591 Record *R = Operand->getValueAsDef("Type");
1592 const CodeGenTarget &T = TP.getDAGPatterns().getTargetInfo();
1593 return UpdateNodeType(ResNo, getValueTypeByHwMode(R, T.getHwModes()), TP);
1594 }
1595
1596 // PointerLikeRegClass has a type that is determined at runtime.
1597 if (Operand->isSubClassOf("PointerLikeRegClass"))
1598 return UpdateNodeType(ResNo, MVT::iPTR, TP);
1599
1600 // Both RegisterClass and RegisterOperand operands derive their types from a
1601 // register class def.
1602 Record *RC = nullptr;
1603 if (Operand->isSubClassOf("RegisterClass"))
1604 RC = Operand;
1605 else if (Operand->isSubClassOf("RegisterOperand"))
1606 RC = Operand->getValueAsDef("RegClass");
1607
1608 assert(RC && "Unknown operand type");
1609 CodeGenTarget &Tgt = TP.getDAGPatterns().getTargetInfo();
1610 return UpdateNodeType(ResNo, Tgt.getRegisterClass(RC).getValueTypes(), TP);
1611}
1612
1613bool TreePatternNode::ContainsUnresolvedType(TreePattern &TP) const {
1614 for (unsigned i = 0, e = Types.size(); i != e; ++i)
1615 if (!TP.getInfer().isConcrete(Types[i], true))
1616 return true;
1617 for (unsigned i = 0, e = getNumChildren(); i != e; ++i)
1618 if (getChild(i)->ContainsUnresolvedType(TP))
1619 return true;
1620 return false;
1621}
1622
1623bool TreePatternNode::hasProperTypeByHwMode() const {
1624 for (const TypeSetByHwMode &S : Types)
1625 if (!S.isDefaultOnly())
1626 return true;
1627 for (const TreePatternNodePtr &C : Children)
1628 if (C->hasProperTypeByHwMode())
1629 return true;
1630 return false;
1631}
1632
1633bool TreePatternNode::hasPossibleType() const {
1634 for (const TypeSetByHwMode &S : Types)
1635 if (!S.isPossible())
1636 return false;
1637 for (const TreePatternNodePtr &C : Children)
1638 if (!C->hasPossibleType())
1639 return false;
1640 return true;
1641}
1642
1643bool TreePatternNode::setDefaultMode(unsigned Mode) {
1644 for (TypeSetByHwMode &S : Types) {
1645 S.makeSimple(Mode);
1646 // Check if the selected mode had a type conflict.
1647 if (S.get(DefaultMode).empty())
1648 return false;
1649 }
1650 for (const TreePatternNodePtr &C : Children)
1651 if (!C->setDefaultMode(Mode))
1652 return false;
1653 return true;
1654}

1656//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
1657// SDNodeInfo implementation
1658//
1659SDNodeInfo::SDNodeInfo(Record *R, const CodeGenHwModes &CGH) : Def(R) {
1660 EnumName = R->getValueAsString("Opcode");
1661 SDClassName = R->getValueAsString("SDClass");
1662 Record *TypeProfile = R->getValueAsDef("TypeProfile");
1663 NumResults = TypeProfile->getValueAsInt("NumResults");
1664 NumOperands = TypeProfile->getValueAsInt("NumOperands");
1665
1666 // Parse the properties.
1667 Properties = parseSDPatternOperatorProperties(R);
1668
1669 // Parse the type constraints.
1670 std::vector<Record*> ConstraintList =
1671 TypeProfile->getValueAsListOfDefs("Constraints");
1672 for (Record *R : ConstraintList)
1673 TypeConstraints.emplace_back(R, CGH);
1674}

1676/// getKnownType - If the type constraints on this node imply a fixed type
1677/// (e.g. all stores return void, etc), then return it as an
1678/// MVT::SimpleValueType. Otherwise, return EEVT::Other.
1679MVT::SimpleValueType SDNodeInfo::getKnownType(unsigned ResNo) const {
1680 unsigned NumResults = getNumResults();
1681 assert(NumResults <= 1 &&
1682 "We only work with nodes with zero or one result so far!");
1683 assert(ResNo == 0 && "Only handles single result nodes so far");
1684
1685 for (const SDTypeConstraint &Constraint : TypeConstraints) {
1686 // Make sure that this applies to the correct node result.
1687 if (Constraint.OperandNo >= NumResults) // FIXME: need value #
1688 continue;
1689
1690 switch (Constraint.ConstraintType) {
1691 default: break;
1692 case SDTypeConstraint::SDTCisVT:
1693 if (Constraint.VVT.isSimple())
1694 return Constraint.VVT.getSimple().SimpleTy;
1695 break;
1696 case SDTypeConstraint::SDTCisPtrTy:
1697 return MVT::iPTR;
1698 }
1699 }
1700 return MVT::Other;
1701}

1703//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
1704// TreePatternNode implementation
1705//
1706
1707static unsigned GetNumNodeResults(Record *Operator, CodeGenDAGPatterns &CDP) {
1708 if (Operator->getName() == "set" ||
1709 Operator->getName() == "implicit")
1710 return 0; // All return nothing.
1711
1712 if (Operator->isSubClassOf("Intrinsic"))
1713 return CDP.getIntrinsic(Operator).IS.RetVTs.size();
1714
1715 if (Operator->isSubClassOf("SDNode"))
1716 return CDP.getSDNodeInfo(Operator).getNumResults();
1717
1718 if (Operator->isSubClassOf("PatFrags")) {
1719 // If we've already parsed this pattern fragment, get it. Otherwise, handle
1720 // the forward reference case where one pattern fragment references another
1721 // before it is processed.
1722 if (TreePattern *PFRec = CDP.getPatternFragmentIfRead(Operator)) {
1723 // The number of results of a fragment with alternative records is the
1724 // maximum number of results across all alternatives.
1725 unsigned NumResults = 0;
1726 for (auto T : PFRec->getTrees())
1727 NumResults = std::max(NumResults, T->getNumTypes());
1728 return NumResults;
1729 }
1730
1731 ListInit *LI = Operator->getValueAsListInit("Fragments");
1732 assert(LI && "Invalid Fragment");
1733 unsigned NumResults = 0;
1734 for (Init *I : LI->getValues()) {
1735 Record *Op = nullptr;
1736 if (DagInit *Dag = dyn_cast<DagInit>(I))
1737 if (DefInit *DI = dyn_cast<DefInit>(Dag->getOperator()))
1738 Op = DI->getDef();
1739 assert(Op && "Invalid Fragment");
1740 NumResults = std::max(NumResults, GetNumNodeResults(Op, CDP));
1741 }
1742 return NumResults;
1743 }
1744
1745 if (Operator->isSubClassOf("Instruction")) {
1746 CodeGenInstruction &InstInfo = CDP.getTargetInfo().getInstruction(Operator);
1747
1748 unsigned NumDefsToAdd = InstInfo.Operands.NumDefs;
1749
1750 // Subtract any defaulted outputs.
1751 for (unsigned i = 0; i != InstInfo.Operands.NumDefs; ++i) {
1752 Record *OperandNode = InstInfo.Operands[i].Rec;
1753
1754 if (OperandNode->isSubClassOf("OperandWithDefaultOps") &&
1755 !CDP.getDefaultOperand(OperandNode).DefaultOps.empty())
1756 --NumDefsToAdd;
1757 }
1758
1759 // Add on one implicit def if it has a resolvable type.
1760 if (InstInfo.HasOneImplicitDefWithKnownVT(CDP.getTargetInfo()) !=MVT::Other)
1761 ++NumDefsToAdd;
1762 return NumDefsToAdd;
1763 }
1764
1765 if (Operator->isSubClassOf("SDNodeXForm"))
1766 return 1; // FIXME: Generalize SDNodeXForm
1767
1768 if (Operator->isSubClassOf("ValueType"))
1769 return 1; // A type-cast of one result.
1770
1771 if (Operator->isSubClassOf("ComplexPattern"))
1772 return 1;
1773
1774 errs() << *Operator;
1775 PrintFatalError("Unhandled node in GetNumNodeResults");
1776}
1777
1778void TreePatternNode::print(raw_ostream &OS) const {
1779 if (isLeaf())
1780 OS << *getLeafValue();
1781 else
1782 OS << '(' << getOperator()->getName();
1783
1784 for (unsigned i = 0, e = Types.size(); i != e; ++i) {
1785 OS << ':';
1786 getExtType(i).writeToStream(OS);
1787 }
1788
1789 if (!isLeaf()) {
1790 if (getNumChildren() != 0) {
1791 OS << " ";
1792 getChild(0)->print(OS);
1793 for (unsigned i = 1, e = getNumChildren(); i != e; ++i) {
1794 OS << ", ";
1795 getChild(i)->print(OS);
1796 }
1797 }
1798 OS << ")";
1799 }
1800
1801 for (const TreePredicateCall &Pred : PredicateCalls) {
1802 OS << "<<P:";
1803 if (Pred.Scope)
1804 OS << Pred.Scope << ":";
1805 OS << Pred.Fn.getFnName() << ">>";
1806 }
1807 if (TransformFn)
1808 OS << "<<X:" << TransformFn->getName() << ">>";
1809 if (!getName().empty())
1810 OS << ":$" << getName();
1811
1812 for (const ScopedName &Name : NamesAsPredicateArg)
1813 OS << ":$pred:" << Name.getScope() << ":" << Name.getIdentifier();
1814}
1815void TreePatternNode::dump() const {
1816 print(errs());
1817}

1819/// isIsomorphicTo - Return true if this node is recursively
1820/// isomorphic to the specified node. For this comparison, the node's
1821/// entire state is considered. The assigned name is ignored, since
1822/// nodes with differing names are considered isomorphic. However, if
1823/// the assigned name is present in the dependent variable set, then
1824/// the assigned name is considered significant and the node is
1825/// isomorphic if the names match.
1826bool TreePatternNode::isIsomorphicTo(const TreePatternNode *N,
1827 const MultipleUseVarSet &DepVars) const {
1828 if (N == this) return true;
1829 if (N->isLeaf() != isLeaf() || getExtTypes() != N->getExtTypes() ||
1830 getPredicateCalls() != N->getPredicateCalls() ||
1831 getTransformFn() != N->getTransformFn())
1832 return false;
1833
1834 if (isLeaf()) {
1835 if (DefInit *DI = dyn_cast<DefInit>(getLeafValue())) {
1836 if (DefInit *NDI = dyn_cast<DefInit>(N->getLeafValue())) {
1837 return ((DI->getDef() == NDI->getDef())
1838 && (DepVars.find(getName()) == DepVars.end()
1839 || getName() == N->getName()));
1840 }
1841 }
1842 return getLeafValue() == N->getLeafValue();
1843 }
1844
1845 if (N->getOperator() != getOperator() ||
1846 N->getNumChildren() != getNumChildren()) return false;
1847 for (unsigned i = 0, e = getNumChildren(); i != e; ++i)
1848 if (!getChild(i)->isIsomorphicTo(N->getChild(i), DepVars))
1849 return false;
1850 return true;
1851}
1852
1853/// clone - Make a copy of this tree and all of its children.
1854///
1855TreePatternNodePtr TreePatternNode::clone() const {
1856 TreePatternNodePtr New;
1857 if (isLeaf()) {
1858 New = std::make_shared<TreePatternNode>(getLeafValue(), getNumTypes());
1859 } else {
1860 std::vector<TreePatternNodePtr> CChildren;
1861 CChildren.reserve(Children.size());
1862 for (unsigned i = 0, e = getNumChildren(); i != e; ++i)
1863 CChildren.push_back(getChild(i)->clone());
1864 New = std::make_shared<TreePatternNode>(getOperator(), std::move(CChildren),
1865 getNumTypes());
1866 }
1867 New->setName(getName());
1868 New->setNamesAsPredicateArg(getNamesAsPredicateArg());
1869 New->Types = Types;
1870 New->setPredicateCalls(getPredicateCalls());
1871 New->setTransformFn(getTransformFn());
1872 return New;
1873}
1874
1875/// RemoveAllTypes - Recursively strip all the types of this tree.
1876void TreePatternNode::RemoveAllTypes() {
1877 // Reset to unknown type.
1878 std::fill(Types.begin(), Types.end(), TypeSetByHwMode());
1879 if (isLeaf()) return;
1880 for (unsigned i = 0, e = getNumChildren(); i != e; ++i)
1881 getChild(i)->RemoveAllTypes();
1882}

1885/// SubstituteFormalArguments - Replace the formal arguments in this tree
1886/// with actual values specified by ArgMap.
1887void TreePatternNode::SubstituteFormalArguments(
1888 std::map<std::string, TreePatternNodePtr> &ArgMap) {
1889 if (isLeaf()) return;
1890
1891 for (unsigned i = 0, e = getNumChildren(); i != e; ++i) {
1892 TreePatternNode *Child = getChild(i);
1893 if (Child->isLeaf()) {
1894 Init *Val = Child->getLeafValue();
1895 // Note that, when substituting into an output pattern, Val might be an
1896 // UnsetInit.
1897 if (isa<UnsetInit>(Val) || (isa<DefInit>(Val) &&
1898 cast<DefInit>(Val)->getDef()->getName() == "node")) {
1899 // We found a use of a formal argument, replace it with its value.
1900 TreePatternNodePtr NewChild = ArgMap[Child->getName()];
1901 assert(NewChild && "Couldn't find formal argument!");
1902 assert((Child->getPredicateCalls().empty() ||
1903 NewChild->getPredicateCalls() == Child->getPredicateCalls()) &&
1904 "Non-empty child predicate clobbered!");
1905 setChild(i, std::move(NewChild));
1906 }
1907 } else {
1908 getChild(i)->SubstituteFormalArguments(ArgMap);
1909 }
1910 }
1911}

1914/// InlinePatternFragments - If this pattern refers to any pattern
1915/// fragments, return the set of inlined versions (this can be more than
1916/// one if a PatFrags record has multiple alternatives).
1917void TreePatternNode::InlinePatternFragments(
1918 TreePatternNodePtr T, TreePattern &TP,
1919 std::vector<TreePatternNodePtr> &OutAlternatives) {
1920
1921 if (TP.hasError())
1922 return;
1923
1924 if (isLeaf()) {
1925 OutAlternatives.push_back(T); // nothing to do.
1926 return;
1927 }
1928
1929 Record *Op = getOperator();
1930
1931 if (!Op->isSubClassOf("PatFrags")) {
1932 if (getNumChildren() == 0) {
1933 OutAlternatives.push_back(T);
1934 return;
1935 }
1936
1937 // Recursively inline children nodes.
1938 std::vector<std::vector<TreePatternNodePtr> > ChildAlternatives;
1939 ChildAlternatives.resize(getNumChildren());
1940 for (unsigned i = 0, e = getNumChildren(); i != e; ++i) {
1941 TreePatternNodePtr Child = getChildShared(i);
1942 Child->InlinePatternFragments(Child, TP, ChildAlternatives[i]);
1943 // If there are no alternatives for any child, there are no
1944 // alternatives for this expression as whole.
1945 if (ChildAlternatives[i].empty())
1946 return;
1947
1948 for (auto NewChild : ChildAlternatives[i])
1949 assert((Child->getPredicateCalls().empty() ||
1950 NewChild->getPredicateCalls() == Child->getPredicateCalls()) &&
1951 "Non-empty child predicate clobbered!");
1952 }
1953
1954 // The end result is an all-pairs construction of the resultant pattern.
1955 std::vector<unsigned> Idxs;
1956 Idxs.resize(ChildAlternatives.size());
1957 bool NotDone;
1958 do {
1959 // Create the variant and add it to the output list.
1960 std::vector<TreePatternNodePtr> NewChildren;
1961 for (unsigned i = 0, e = ChildAlternatives.size(); i != e; ++i)
1962 NewChildren.push_back(ChildAlternatives[i][Idxs[i]]);
1963 TreePatternNodePtr R = std::make_shared<TreePatternNode>(
1964 getOperator(), std::move(NewChildren), getNumTypes());
1965
1966 // Copy over properties.
1967 R->setName(getName());
1968 R->setNamesAsPredicateArg(getNamesAsPredicateArg());
1969 R->setPredicateCalls(getPredicateCalls());
1970 R->setTransformFn(getTransformFn());
1971 for (unsigned i = 0, e = getNumTypes(); i != e; ++i)
1972 R->setType(i, getExtType(i));
1973 for (unsigned i = 0, e = getNumResults(); i != e; ++i)
1974 R->setResultIndex(i, getResultIndex(i));
1975
1976 // Register alternative.
1977 OutAlternatives.push_back(R);
1978
1979 // Increment indices to the next permutation by incrementing the
1980 // indices from last index backward, e.g., generate the sequence
1981 // [0, 0], [0, 1], [1, 0], [1, 1].
1982 int IdxsIdx;
1983 for (IdxsIdx = Idxs.size() - 1; IdxsIdx >= 0; --IdxsIdx) {
1984 if (++Idxs[IdxsIdx] == ChildAlternatives[IdxsIdx].size())
1985 Idxs[IdxsIdx] = 0;
1986 else
1987 break;
1988 }
1989 NotDone = (IdxsIdx >= 0);
1990 } while (NotDone);
1991
1992 return;
1993 }
1994
1995 // Otherwise, we found a reference to a fragment. First, look up its
1996 // TreePattern record.
1997 TreePattern *Frag = TP.getDAGPatterns().getPatternFragment(Op);
1998
1999 // Verify that we are passing the right number of operands.
2000 if (Frag->getNumArgs() != Children.size()) {
2001 TP.error("'" + Op->getName() + "' fragment requires " +
2002 Twine(Frag->getNumArgs()) + " operands!");
2003 return;
2004 }
2005
2006 TreePredicateFn PredFn(Frag);
2007 unsigned Scope = 0;
2008 if (TreePredicateFn(Frag).usesOperands())
2009 Scope = TP.getDAGPatterns().allocateScope();
2010
2011 // Compute the map of formal to actual arguments.
2012 std::map<std::string, TreePatternNodePtr> ArgMap;
2013 for (unsigned i = 0, e = Frag->getNumArgs(); i != e; ++i) {
2014 TreePatternNodePtr Child = getChildShared(i);
2015 if (Scope != 0) {
2016 Child = Child->clone();
2017 Child->addNameAsPredicateArg(ScopedName(Scope, Frag->getArgName(i)));
2018 }
2019 ArgMap[Frag->getArgName(i)] = Child;
2020 }
2021
2022 // Loop over all fragment alternatives.
2023 for (auto Alternative : Frag->getTrees()) {
2024 TreePatternNodePtr FragTree = Alternative->clone();
2025
2026 if (!PredFn.isAlwaysTrue())
2027 FragTree->addPredicateCall(PredFn, Scope);
2028
2029 // Resolve formal arguments to their actual value.
2030 if (Frag->getNumArgs())
2031 FragTree->SubstituteFormalArguments(ArgMap);
2032
2033 // Transfer types. Note that the resolved alternative may have fewer
2034 // (but not more) results than the PatFrags node.
2035 FragTree->setName(getName());
2036 for (unsigned i = 0, e = FragTree->getNumTypes(); i != e; ++i)
2037 FragTree->UpdateNodeType(i, getExtType(i), TP);
2038
2039 // Transfer in the old predicates.
2040 for (const TreePredicateCall &Pred : getPredicateCalls())
2041 FragTree->addPredicateCall(Pred);
2042
2043 // The fragment we inlined could have recursive inlining that is needed. See
2044 // if there are any pattern fragments in it and inline them as needed.
2045 FragTree->InlinePatternFragments(FragTree, TP, OutAlternatives);
2046 }
2047}

2049/// getImplicitType - Check to see if the specified record has an implicit
2050/// type which should be applied to it. This will infer the type of register
2051/// references from the register file information, for example.
2052///
2053/// When Unnamed is set, return the type of a DAG operand with no name, such as
2054/// the F8RC register class argument in:
2055///
2056/// (COPY_TO_REGCLASS GPR:$src, F8RC)
2057///
2058/// When Unnamed is false, return the type of a named DAG operand such as the
2059/// GPR:$src operand above.
2060///
2061static TypeSetByHwMode getImplicitType(Record *R, unsigned ResNo,
2062 bool NotRegisters,
2063 bool Unnamed,
2064 TreePattern &TP) {
2065 CodeGenDAGPatterns &CDP = TP.getDAGPatterns();
2066
2067 // Check to see if this is a register operand.
2068 if (R->isSubClassOf("RegisterOperand")) {
2069 assert(ResNo == 0 && "Regoperand ref only has one result!");
2070 if (NotRegisters)
2071 return TypeSetByHwMode(); // Unknown.
2072 Record *RegClass = R->getValueAsDef("RegClass");
2073 const CodeGenTarget &T = TP.getDAGPatterns().getTargetInfo();
2074 return TypeSetByHwMode(T.getRegisterClass(RegClass).getValueTypes());
2075 }
2076
2077 // Check to see if this is a register or a register class.
2078 if (R->isSubClassOf("RegisterClass")) {
2079 assert(ResNo == 0 && "Regclass ref only has one result!");
2080 // An unnamed register class represents itself as an i32 immediate, for
2081 // example on a COPY_TO_REGCLASS instruction.
2082 if (Unnamed)
2083 return TypeSetByHwMode(MVT::i32);
2084
2085 // In a named operand, the register class provides the possible set of
2086 // types.
2087 if (NotRegisters)
2088 return TypeSetByHwMode(); // Unknown.
2089 const CodeGenTarget &T = TP.getDAGPatterns().getTargetInfo();
2090 return TypeSetByHwMode(T.getRegisterClass(R).getValueTypes());
2091 }
2092
2093 if (R->isSubClassOf("PatFrags")) {
2094 assert(ResNo == 0 && "FIXME: PatFrag with multiple results?");
2095 // Pattern fragment types will be resolved when they are inlined.
2096 return TypeSetByHwMode(); // Unknown.
2097 }
2098
2099 if (R->isSubClassOf("Register")) {
2100 assert(ResNo == 0 && "Registers only produce one result!");
2101 if (NotRegisters)
2102 return TypeSetByHwMode(); // Unknown.
2103 const CodeGenTarget &T = TP.getDAGPatterns().getTargetInfo();
2104 return TypeSetByHwMode(T.getRegisterVTs(R));
2105 }
2106
2107 if (R->isSubClassOf("SubRegIndex")) {
2108 assert(ResNo == 0 && "SubRegisterIndices only produce one result!");
2109 return TypeSetByHwMode(MVT::i32);
2110 }
2111
2112 if (R->isSubClassOf("ValueType")) {
2113 assert(ResNo == 0 && "This node only has one result!");
2114 // An unnamed VTSDNode represents itself as an MVT::Other immediate.
2115 //
2116 // (sext_inreg GPR:$src, i16)
2117 // ~~~
2118 if (Unnamed)
2119 return TypeSetByHwMode(MVT::Other);
2120 // With a name, the ValueType simply provides the type of the named
2121 // variable.
2122 //
2123 // (sext_inreg i32:$src, i16)
2124 // ~~~~~~~~
2125 if (NotRegisters)
2126 return TypeSetByHwMode(); // Unknown.
2127 const CodeGenHwModes &CGH = CDP.getTargetInfo().getHwModes();
2128 return TypeSetByHwMode(getValueTypeByHwMode(R, CGH));
2129 }
2130
2131 if (R->isSubClassOf("CondCode")) {
2132 assert(ResNo == 0 && "This node only has one result!");
2133 // Using a CondCodeSDNode.
2134 return TypeSetByHwMode(MVT::Other);
2135 }
2136
2137 if (R->isSubClassOf("ComplexPattern")) {
2138 assert(ResNo == 0 && "FIXME: ComplexPattern with multiple results?");
2139 if (NotRegisters)
2140 return TypeSetByHwMode(); // Unknown.
2141 return TypeSetByHwMode(CDP.getComplexPattern(R).getValueType());
2142 }
2143 if (R->isSubClassOf("PointerLikeRegClass")) {
2144 assert(ResNo == 0 && "Regclass can only have one result!");
2145 TypeSetByHwMode VTS(MVT::iPTR);
2146 TP.getInfer().expandOverloads(VTS);
2147 return VTS;
2148 }
2149
2150 if (R->getName() == "node" || R->getName() == "srcvalue" ||
2151 R->getName() == "zero_reg" || R->getName() == "immAllOnesV" ||
2152 R->getName() == "immAllZerosV" || R->getName() == "undef_tied_input") {
2153 // Placeholder.
2154 return TypeSetByHwMode(); // Unknown.
2155 }
2156
2157 if (R->isSubClassOf("Operand")) {
2158 const CodeGenHwModes &CGH = CDP.getTargetInfo().getHwModes();
2159 Record *T = R->getValueAsDef("Type");
2160 return TypeSetByHwMode(getValueTypeByHwMode(T, CGH));
2161 }
2162
2163 TP.error("Unknown node flavor used in pattern: " + R->getName());
2164 return TypeSetByHwMode(MVT::Other);
2165}

2181/// getComplexPatternInfo - If this node corresponds to a ComplexPattern,
2182/// return the ComplexPattern information, otherwise return null.
2183const ComplexPattern *
2184TreePatternNode::getComplexPatternInfo(const CodeGenDAGPatterns &CGP) const {

2188 if (!DI)
2189 return nullptr;
2190 Rec = DI->getDef();

2199unsigned TreePatternNode::getNumMIResults(const CodeGenDAGPatterns &CGP) const {
2200 // A ComplexPattern specifically declares how many results it fills in.
2201 if (const ComplexPattern *CP = getComplexPatternInfo(CGP))
2202 return CP->getNumOperands();
2203
2204 // If MIOperandInfo is specified, that gives the count.
2205 if (isLeaf()) {
2206 DefInit *DI = dyn_cast<DefInit>(getLeafValue());
2207 if (DI && DI->getDef()->isSubClassOf("Operand")) {
2208 DagInit *MIOps = DI->getDef()->getValueAsDag("MIOperandInfo");
2209 if (MIOps->getNumArgs())
2210 return MIOps->getNumArgs();
2211 }
2212 }
2213
2214 // Otherwise there is just one result.
2215 return 1;
2216}

2218/// NodeHasProperty - Return true if this node has the specified property.
2219bool TreePatternNode::NodeHasProperty(SDNP Property,
2220 const CodeGenDAGPatterns &CGP) const {
2221 if (isLeaf()) {
2222 if (const ComplexPattern *CP = getComplexPatternInfo(CGP))
2223 return CP->hasProperty(Property);
2224
2225 return false;
2226 }
2227
2228 if (Property != SDNPHasChain) {
2229 // The chain proprety is already present on the different intrinsic node
2230 // types (intrinsic_w_chain, intrinsic_void), and is not explicitly listed
2231 // on the intrinsic. Anything else is specific to the individual intrinsic.
2232 if (const CodeGenIntrinsic *Int = getIntrinsicInfo(CGP))
2233 return Int->hasProperty(Property);
2234 }
2235
2236 if (!Operator->isSubClassOf("SDPatternOperator"))
2237 return false;
2238
2239 return CGP.getSDNodeInfo(Operator).hasProperty(Property);
2240}
