2292/// ApplyTypeConstraints - Apply all of the type constraints relevant to
2293/// this node and its children in the tree. This returns true if it makes a
2294/// change, false otherwise. If a type contradiction is found, flag an error.
2295bool TreePatternNode::ApplyTypeConstraints(TreePattern &TP, bool NotRegisters) {
2296 if (TP.hasError())
2297 return false;
2298
2299 CodeGenDAGPatterns &CDP = TP.getDAGPatterns();
2300 if (isLeaf()) {
2301 if (DefInit *DI = dyn_cast<DefInit>(getLeafValue())) {
2302 // If it's a regclass or something else known, include the type.
2303 bool MadeChange = false;
2304 for (unsigned i = 0, e = Types.size(); i != e; ++i)
2305 MadeChange |= UpdateNodeType(i, getImplicitType(DI->getDef(), i,
2306 NotRegisters,
2307 !hasName(), TP), TP);
2308 return MadeChange;
2309 }
2310
2311 if (IntInit *II = dyn_cast<IntInit>(getLeafValue())) {
2312 assert(Types.size() == 1 && "Invalid IntInit");
2313
2314 // Int inits are always integers. :)
2315 bool MadeChange = TP.getInfer().EnforceInteger(Types[0]);
2316
2317 if (!TP.getInfer().isConcrete(Types[0], false))
2318 return MadeChange;
2319
2320 ValueTypeByHwMode VVT = TP.getInfer().getConcrete(Types[0], false);
2321 for (auto &P : VVT) {
2322 MVT::SimpleValueType VT = P.second.SimpleTy;
2323 if (VT == MVT::iPTR || VT == MVT::iPTRAny)
2324 continue;
2325 unsigned Size = MVT(VT).getSizeInBits();
2326 // Make sure that the value is representable for this type.
2327 if (Size >= 32)
2328 continue;
2329 // Check that the value doesn't use more bits than we have. It must
2330 // either be a sign- or zero-extended equivalent of the original.
2331 int64_t SignBitAndAbove = II->getValue() >> (Size - 1);
2332 if (SignBitAndAbove == -1 || SignBitAndAbove == 0 ||
2333 SignBitAndAbove == 1)
2334 continue;
2335
2336 TP.error("Integer value '" + Twine(II->getValue()) +
2337 "' is out of range for type '" + getEnumName(VT) + "'!");
2338 break;
2339 }
2340 return MadeChange;
2341 }
2342
2343 return false;
2344 }
2345
2346 if (const CodeGenIntrinsic *Int = getIntrinsicInfo(CDP)) {
2347 bool MadeChange = false;
2348
2349 // Apply the result type to the node.
2350 unsigned NumRetVTs = Int->IS.RetVTs.size();
2351 unsigned NumParamVTs = Int->IS.ParamVTs.size();
2352
2353 for (unsigned i = 0, e = NumRetVTs; i != e; ++i)
2354 MadeChange |= UpdateNodeType(i, Int->IS.RetVTs[i], TP);
2355
2356 if (getNumChildren() != NumParamVTs + 1) {
2357 TP.error("Intrinsic '" + Int->Name + "' expects " + Twine(NumParamVTs) +
2358 " operands, not " + Twine(getNumChildren() - 1) + " operands!");
2359 return false;
2360 }
2361
2362 // Apply type info to the intrinsic ID.
2363 MadeChange |= getChild(0)->UpdateNodeType(0, MVT::iPTR, TP);
2364
2365 for (unsigned i = 0, e = getNumChildren()-1; i != e; ++i) {
2366 MadeChange |= getChild(i+1)->ApplyTypeConstraints(TP, NotRegisters);
2367
2368 MVT::SimpleValueType OpVT = Int->IS.ParamVTs[i];
2369 assert(getChild(i+1)->getNumTypes() == 1 && "Unhandled case");
2370 MadeChange |= getChild(i+1)->UpdateNodeType(0, OpVT, TP);
2371 }
2372 return MadeChange;
2373 }
2374
2375 if (getOperator()->isSubClassOf("SDNode")) {
2376 const SDNodeInfo &NI = CDP.getSDNodeInfo(getOperator());
2377
2378 // Check that the number of operands is sane. Negative operands -> varargs.
2379 if (NI.getNumOperands() >= 0 &&
2380 getNumChildren() != (unsigned)NI.getNumOperands()) {
2381 TP.error(getOperator()->getName() + " node requires exactly " +
2382 Twine(NI.getNumOperands()) + " operands!");
2383 return false;
2384 }
2385
2386 bool MadeChange = false;
2387 for (unsigned i = 0, e = getNumChildren(); i != e; ++i)
2388 MadeChange |= getChild(i)->ApplyTypeConstraints(TP, NotRegisters);
2389 MadeChange |= NI.ApplyTypeConstraints(this, TP);
2390 return MadeChange;
2391 }
2392
2393 if (getOperator()->isSubClassOf("Instruction")) {
2394 const DAGInstruction &Inst = CDP.getInstruction(getOperator());
2395 CodeGenInstruction &InstInfo =
2396 CDP.getTargetInfo().getInstruction(getOperator());
2397
2398 bool MadeChange = false;
2399
2400 // Apply the result types to the node, these come from the things in the
2401 // (outs) list of the instruction.
2402 unsigned NumResultsToAdd = std::min(InstInfo.Operands.NumDefs,
2403 Inst.getNumResults());
2404 for (unsigned ResNo = 0; ResNo != NumResultsToAdd; ++ResNo)
2405 MadeChange |= UpdateNodeTypeFromInst(ResNo, Inst.getResult(ResNo), TP);
2406
2407 // If the instruction has implicit defs, we apply the first one as a result.
2408 // FIXME: This sucks, it should apply all implicit defs.
2409 if (!InstInfo.ImplicitDefs.empty()) {
2410 unsigned ResNo = NumResultsToAdd;
2411
2412 // FIXME: Generalize to multiple possible types and multiple possible
2413 // ImplicitDefs.
2414 MVT::SimpleValueType VT =
2415 InstInfo.HasOneImplicitDefWithKnownVT(CDP.getTargetInfo());
2416
2417 if (VT != MVT::Other)
2418 MadeChange |= UpdateNodeType(ResNo, VT, TP);
2419 }
2420
2421 // If this is an INSERT_SUBREG, constrain the source and destination VTs to
2422 // be the same.
2423 if (getOperator()->getName() == "INSERT_SUBREG") {
2424 assert(getChild(0)->getNumTypes() == 1 && "FIXME: Unhandled");
2425 MadeChange |= UpdateNodeType(0, getChild(0)->getExtType(0), TP);
2426 MadeChange |= getChild(0)->UpdateNodeType(0, getExtType(0), TP);
2427 } else if (getOperator()->getName() == "REG_SEQUENCE") {
2428 // We need to do extra, custom typechecking for REG_SEQUENCE since it is
2429 // variadic.
2430
2431 unsigned NChild = getNumChildren();
2432 if (NChild < 3) {
2433 TP.error("REG_SEQUENCE requires at least 3 operands!");
2434 return false;
2435 }
2436
2437 if (NChild % 2 == 0) {
2438 TP.error("REG_SEQUENCE requires an odd number of operands!");
2439 return false;
2440 }
2441
2442 if (!isOperandClass(getChild(0), "RegisterClass")) {
2443 TP.error("REG_SEQUENCE requires a RegisterClass for first operand!");
2444 return false;
2445 }
2446
2447 for (unsigned I = 1; I < NChild; I += 2) {
2448 TreePatternNode *SubIdxChild = getChild(I + 1);
2449 if (!isOperandClass(SubIdxChild, "SubRegIndex")) {
2450 TP.error("REG_SEQUENCE requires a SubRegIndex for operand " +
2451 Twine(I + 1) + "!");
2452 return false;
2453 }
2454 }
2455 }
2456
2457 unsigned ChildNo = 0;
2458 for (unsigned i = 0, e = Inst.getNumOperands(); i != e; ++i) {
2459 Record *OperandNode = Inst.getOperand(i);
2460
2461 // If the instruction expects a predicate or optional def operand, we
2462 // codegen this by setting the operand to it's default value if it has a
2463 // non-empty DefaultOps field.
2464 if (OperandNode->isSubClassOf("OperandWithDefaultOps") &&
2465 !CDP.getDefaultOperand(OperandNode).DefaultOps.empty())
2466 continue;
2467
2468 // Verify that we didn't run out of provided operands.
2469 if (ChildNo >= getNumChildren()) {
2470 emitTooFewOperandsError(TP, getOperator()->getName(), getNumChildren());
2471 return false;
2472 }
2473
2474 TreePatternNode *Child = getChild(ChildNo++);
2475 unsigned ChildResNo = 0; // Instructions always use res #0 of their op.
2476
2477 // If the operand has sub-operands, they may be provided by distinct
2478 // child patterns, so attempt to match each sub-operand separately.
2479 if (OperandNode->isSubClassOf("Operand")) {
2480 DagInit *MIOpInfo = OperandNode->getValueAsDag("MIOperandInfo");
2481 if (unsigned NumArgs = MIOpInfo->getNumArgs()) {
2482 // But don't do that if the whole operand is being provided by
2483 // a single ComplexPattern-related Operand.
2484
2485 if (Child->getNumMIResults(CDP) < NumArgs) {
2486 // Match first sub-operand against the child we already have.
2487 Record *SubRec = cast<DefInit>(MIOpInfo->getArg(0))->getDef();
2488 MadeChange |=
2489 Child->UpdateNodeTypeFromInst(ChildResNo, SubRec, TP);
2490
2491 // And the remaining sub-operands against subsequent children.
2492 for (unsigned Arg = 1; Arg < NumArgs; ++Arg) {
2493 if (ChildNo >= getNumChildren()) {
2494 emitTooFewOperandsError(TP, getOperator()->getName(),
2495 getNumChildren());
2496 return false;
2497 }
2498 Child = getChild(ChildNo++);
2499
2500 SubRec = cast<DefInit>(MIOpInfo->getArg(Arg))->getDef();
2501 MadeChange |=
2502 Child->UpdateNodeTypeFromInst(ChildResNo, SubRec, TP);
2503 }
2504 continue;
2505 }
2506 }
2507 }
2508
2509 // If we didn't match by pieces above, attempt to match the whole
2510 // operand now.
2511 MadeChange |= Child->UpdateNodeTypeFromInst(ChildResNo, OperandNode, TP);
2512 }
2513
2514 if (!InstInfo.Operands.isVariadic && ChildNo != getNumChildren()) {
2515 emitTooManyOperandsError(TP, getOperator()->getName(),
2516 ChildNo, getNumChildren());
2517 return false;
2518 }
2519
2520 for (unsigned i = 0, e = getNumChildren(); i != e; ++i)
2521 MadeChange |= getChild(i)->ApplyTypeConstraints(TP, NotRegisters);
2522 return MadeChange;
2523 }
2524
2525 if (getOperator()->isSubClassOf("ComplexPattern")) {
2526 bool MadeChange = false;
2527
2528 for (unsigned i = 0; i < getNumChildren(); ++i)
2529 MadeChange |= getChild(i)->ApplyTypeConstraints(TP, NotRegisters);
2530
2531 return MadeChange;
2532 }
2533
2534 assert(getOperator()->isSubClassOf("SDNodeXForm") && "Unknown node type!");
2535
2536 // Node transforms always take one operand.
2537 if (getNumChildren() != 1) {
2538 TP.error("Node transform '" + getOperator()->getName() +
2539 "' requires one operand!");
2540 return false;
2541 }
2542
2543 bool MadeChange = getChild(0)->ApplyTypeConstraints(TP, NotRegisters);
2544 return MadeChange;
2545}
2546
2547/// OnlyOnRHSOfCommutative - Return true if this value is only allowed on the
2548/// RHS of a commutative operation, not the on LHS.
2549static bool OnlyOnRHSOfCommutative(TreePatternNode *N) {
2550 if (!N->isLeaf() && N->getOperator()->getName() == "imm")
2551 return true;
2552 if (N->isLeaf() && isa<IntInit>(N->getLeafValue()))
2553 return true;
2554 return false;
2555}
2556
2557
2558/// canPatternMatch - If it is impossible for this pattern to match on this
2559/// target, fill in Reason and return false. Otherwise, return true. This is
2560/// used as a sanity check for .td files (to prevent people from writing stuff
2561/// that can never possibly work), and to prevent the pattern permuter from
2562/// generating stuff that is useless.
2563bool TreePatternNode::canPatternMatch(std::string &Reason,
2564 const CodeGenDAGPatterns &CDP) {
2565 if (isLeaf()) return true;
2566
2567 for (unsigned i = 0, e = getNumChildren(); i != e; ++i)
2568 if (!getChild(i)->canPatternMatch(Reason, CDP))
2569 return false;
2570
2571 // If this is an intrinsic, handle cases that would make it not match. For
2572 // example, if an operand is required to be an immediate.
2573 if (getOperator()->isSubClassOf("Intrinsic")) {
2574 // TODO:
2575 return true;
2576 }
2577
2578 if (getOperator()->isSubClassOf("ComplexPattern"))
2579 return true;
2580
2581 // If this node is a commutative operator, check that the LHS isn't an
2582 // immediate.
2583 const SDNodeInfo &NodeInfo = CDP.getSDNodeInfo(getOperator());
2584 bool isCommIntrinsic = isCommutativeIntrinsic(CDP);
2585 if (NodeInfo.hasProperty(SDNPCommutative) || isCommIntrinsic) {
2586 // Scan all of the operands of the node and make sure that only the last one
2587 // is a constant node, unless the RHS also is.
2588 if (!OnlyOnRHSOfCommutative(getChild(getNumChildren()-1))) {
2589 unsigned Skip = isCommIntrinsic ? 1 : 0; // First operand is intrinsic id.
2590 for (unsigned i = Skip, e = getNumChildren()-1; i != e; ++i)
2591 if (OnlyOnRHSOfCommutative(getChild(i))) {
2592 Reason="Immediate value must be on the RHS of commutative operators!";
2593 return false;
2594 }
2595 }
2596 }
2597
2598 return true;
2599}

2647
2648TreePatternNodePtr TreePattern::ParseTreePattern(Init *TheInit,
2649 StringRef OpName) {
2650 if (DefInit *DI = dyn_cast<DefInit>(TheInit)) {
2651 Record *R = DI->getDef();
2652
2653 // Direct reference to a leaf DagNode or PatFrag? Turn it into a
2654 // TreePatternNode of its own. For example:
2655 /// (foo GPR, imm) -> (foo GPR, (imm))
2656 if (R->isSubClassOf("SDNode") || R->isSubClassOf("PatFrags"))
2657 return ParseTreePattern(
2658 DagInit::get(DI, nullptr,
2659 std::vector<std::pair<Init*, StringInit*> >()),
2660 OpName);
2661
2662 // Input argument?
2663 TreePatternNodePtr Res = std::make_shared<TreePatternNode>(DI, 1);
2664 if (R->getName() == "node" && !OpName.empty()) {
2665 if (OpName.empty())
2666 error("'node' argument requires a name to match with operand list");
2667 Args.push_back(OpName);
2668 }
2669
2670 Res->setName(OpName);
2671 return Res;
2672 }
2673
2674 // ?:$name or just $name.
2675 if (isa<UnsetInit>(TheInit)) {
2676 if (OpName.empty())
2677 error("'?' argument requires a name to match with operand list");
2678 TreePatternNodePtr Res = std::make_shared<TreePatternNode>(TheInit, 1);
2679 Args.push_back(OpName);
2680 Res->setName(OpName);
2681 return Res;
2682 }
2683
2684 if (isa<IntInit>(TheInit) || isa<BitInit>(TheInit)) {
2685 if (!OpName.empty())
2686 error("Constant int or bit argument should not have a name!");
2687 if (isa<BitInit>(TheInit))
2688 TheInit = TheInit->convertInitializerTo(IntRecTy::get());
2689 return std::make_shared<TreePatternNode>(TheInit, 1);
2690 }
2691
2692 if (BitsInit *BI = dyn_cast<BitsInit>(TheInit)) {
2693 // Turn this into an IntInit.
2694 Init *II = BI->convertInitializerTo(IntRecTy::get());
2695 if (!II || !isa<IntInit>(II))
2696 error("Bits value must be constants!");
2697 return ParseTreePattern(II, OpName);
2698 }
2699
2700 DagInit *Dag = dyn_cast<DagInit>(TheInit);
2701 if (!Dag) {
2702 TheInit->print(errs());
2703 error("Pattern has unexpected init kind!");
2704 }
2705 DefInit *OpDef = dyn_cast<DefInit>(Dag->getOperator());
2706 if (!OpDef) error("Pattern has unexpected operator type!");
2707 Record *Operator = OpDef->getDef();
2708
2709 if (Operator->isSubClassOf("ValueType")) {
2710 // If the operator is a ValueType, then this must be "type cast" of a leaf
2711 // node.
2712 if (Dag->getNumArgs() != 1)
2713 error("Type cast only takes one operand!");
2714
2715 TreePatternNodePtr New =
2716 ParseTreePattern(Dag->getArg(0), Dag->getArgNameStr(0));
2717
2718 // Apply the type cast.
2719 assert(New->getNumTypes() == 1 && "FIXME: Unhandled");
2720 const CodeGenHwModes &CGH = getDAGPatterns().getTargetInfo().getHwModes();
2721 New->UpdateNodeType(0, getValueTypeByHwMode(Operator, CGH), *this);
2722
2723 if (!OpName.empty())
2724 error("ValueType cast should not have a name!");
2725 return New;
2726 }
2727
2728 // Verify that this is something that makes sense for an operator.
2729 if (!Operator->isSubClassOf("PatFrags") &&
2730 !Operator->isSubClassOf("SDNode") &&
2731 !Operator->isSubClassOf("Instruction") &&
2732 !Operator->isSubClassOf("SDNodeXForm") &&
2733 !Operator->isSubClassOf("Intrinsic") &&
2734 !Operator->isSubClassOf("ComplexPattern") &&
2735 Operator->getName() != "set" &&
2736 Operator->getName() != "implicit")
2737 error("Unrecognized node '" + Operator->getName() + "'!");
2738
2739 // Check to see if this is something that is illegal in an input pattern.
2740 if (isInputPattern) {
2741 if (Operator->isSubClassOf("Instruction") ||
2742 Operator->isSubClassOf("SDNodeXForm"))
2743 error("Cannot use '" + Operator->getName() + "' in an input pattern!");
2744 } else {
2745 if (Operator->isSubClassOf("Intrinsic"))
2746 error("Cannot use '" + Operator->getName() + "' in an output pattern!");
2747
2748 if (Operator->isSubClassOf("SDNode") &&
2749 Operator->getName() != "imm" &&
2750 Operator->getName() != "fpimm" &&
2751 Operator->getName() != "tglobaltlsaddr" &&
2752 Operator->getName() != "tconstpool" &&
2753 Operator->getName() != "tjumptable" &&
2754 Operator->getName() != "tframeindex" &&
2755 Operator->getName() != "texternalsym" &&
2756 Operator->getName() != "tblockaddress" &&
2757 Operator->getName() != "tglobaladdr" &&
2758 Operator->getName() != "bb" &&
2759 Operator->getName() != "vt" &&
2760 Operator->getName() != "mcsym")
2761 error("Cannot use '" + Operator->getName() + "' in an output pattern!");
2762 }
2763
2764 std::vector<TreePatternNodePtr> Children;
2765
2766 // Parse all the operands.
2767 for (unsigned i = 0, e = Dag->getNumArgs(); i != e; ++i)
2768 Children.push_back(ParseTreePattern(Dag->getArg(i), Dag->getArgNameStr(i)));
2769
2770 // Get the actual number of results before Operator is converted to an intrinsic
2771 // node (which is hard-coded to have either zero or one result).
2772 unsigned NumResults = GetNumNodeResults(Operator, CDP);
2773
2774 // If the operator is an intrinsic, then this is just syntactic sugar for
2775 // (intrinsic_* <number>, ..children..). Pick the right intrinsic node, and
2776 // convert the intrinsic name to a number.
2777 if (Operator->isSubClassOf("Intrinsic")) {
2778 const CodeGenIntrinsic &Int = getDAGPatterns().getIntrinsic(Operator);
2779 unsigned IID = getDAGPatterns().getIntrinsicID(Operator)+1;
2780
2781 // If this intrinsic returns void, it must have side-effects and thus a
2782 // chain.
2783 if (Int.IS.RetVTs.empty())
2784 Operator = getDAGPatterns().get_intrinsic_void_sdnode();
2785 else if (Int.ModRef != CodeGenIntrinsic::NoMem)
2786 // Has side-effects, requires chain.
2787 Operator = getDAGPatterns().get_intrinsic_w_chain_sdnode();
2788 else // Otherwise, no chain.
2789 Operator = getDAGPatterns().get_intrinsic_wo_chain_sdnode();
2790
2791 Children.insert(Children.begin(),
2792 std::make_shared<TreePatternNode>(IntInit::get(IID), 1));
2793 }
2794
2795 if (Operator->isSubClassOf("ComplexPattern")) {
2796 for (unsigned i = 0; i < Children.size(); ++i) {
2797 TreePatternNodePtr Child = Children[i];
2798
2799 if (Child->getName().empty())
2800 error("All arguments to a ComplexPattern must be named");
2801
2802 // Check that the ComplexPattern uses are consistent: "(MY_PAT $a, $b)"
2803 // and "(MY_PAT $b, $a)" should not be allowed in the same pattern;
2804 // neither should "(MY_PAT_1 $a, $b)" and "(MY_PAT_2 $a, $b)".
2805 auto OperandId = std::make_pair(Operator, i);
2806 auto PrevOp = ComplexPatternOperands.find(Child->getName());
2807 if (PrevOp != ComplexPatternOperands.end()) {
2808 if (PrevOp->getValue() != OperandId)
2809 error("All ComplexPattern operands must appear consistently: "
2810 "in the same order in just one ComplexPattern instance.");
2811 } else
2812 ComplexPatternOperands[Child->getName()] = OperandId;
2813 }
2814 }
2815
2816 TreePatternNodePtr Result =
2817 std::make_shared<TreePatternNode>(Operator, std::move(Children),
2818 NumResults);
2819 Result->setName(OpName);
2820
2821 if (Dag->getName()) {
2822 assert(Result->getName().empty());
2823 Result->setName(Dag->getNameStr());
2824 }
2825 return Result;
2826}
2827
2828/// SimplifyTree - See if we can simplify this tree to eliminate something that
2829/// will never match in favor of something obvious that will. This is here
2830/// strictly as a convenience to target authors because it allows them to write
2831/// more type generic things and have useless type casts fold away.
2832///
2833/// This returns true if any change is made.
2834static bool SimplifyTree(TreePatternNodePtr &N) {
2835 if (N->isLeaf())
2836 return false;
2837
2838 // If we have a bitconvert with a resolved type and if the source and
2839 // destination types are the same, then the bitconvert is useless, remove it.
2840 if (N->getOperator()->getName() == "bitconvert" &&
2841 N->getExtType(0).isValueTypeByHwMode(false) &&
2842 N->getExtType(0) == N->getChild(0)->getExtType(0) &&
2843 N->getName().empty()) {
2844 N = N->getChildShared(0);
2845 SimplifyTree(N);
2846 return true;
2847 }
2848
2849 // Walk all children.
2850 bool MadeChange = false;
2851 for (unsigned i = 0, e = N->getNumChildren(); i != e; ++i) {
2852 TreePatternNodePtr Child = N->getChildShared(i);
2853 MadeChange |= SimplifyTree(Child);
2854 N->setChild(i, std::move(Child));
2855 }
2856 return MadeChange;
2857}
2858
2859
2860
2861/// InferAllTypes - Infer/propagate as many types throughout the expression
2862/// patterns as possible. Return true if all types are inferred, false
2863/// otherwise. Flags an error if a type contradiction is found.
2864bool TreePattern::
2865InferAllTypes(const StringMap<SmallVector<TreePatternNode*,1> > *InNamedTypes) {
2866 if (NamedNodes.empty())
2867 ComputeNamedNodes();
2868
2869 bool MadeChange = true;
2870 while (MadeChange) {
2871 MadeChange = false;
2872 for (TreePatternNodePtr &Tree : Trees) {
2873 MadeChange |= Tree->ApplyTypeConstraints(*this, false);
2874 MadeChange |= SimplifyTree(Tree);
2875 }
2876
2877 // If there are constraints on our named nodes, apply them.
2878 for (auto &Entry : NamedNodes) {
2879 SmallVectorImpl<TreePatternNode*> &Nodes = Entry.second;
2880
2881 // If we have input named node types, propagate their types to the named
2882 // values here.
2883 if (InNamedTypes) {
2884 if (!InNamedTypes->count(Entry.getKey())) {
2885 error("Node '" + std::string(Entry.getKey()) +
2886 "' in output pattern but not input pattern");
2887 return true;
2888 }
2889
2890 const SmallVectorImpl<TreePatternNode*> &InNodes =
2891 InNamedTypes->find(Entry.getKey())->second;
2892
2893 // The input types should be fully resolved by now.
2894 for (TreePatternNode *Node : Nodes) {
2895 // If this node is a register class, and it is the root of the pattern
2896 // then we're mapping something onto an input register. We allow
2897 // changing the type of the input register in this case. This allows
2898 // us to match things like:
2899 // def : Pat<(v1i64 (bitconvert(v2i32 DPR:$src))), (v1i64 DPR:$src)>;
2900 if (Node == Trees[0].get() && Node->isLeaf()) {
2901 DefInit *DI = dyn_cast<DefInit>(Node->getLeafValue());
2902 if (DI && (DI->getDef()->isSubClassOf("RegisterClass") ||
2903 DI->getDef()->isSubClassOf("RegisterOperand")))
2904 continue;
2905 }
2906
2907 assert(Node->getNumTypes() == 1 &&
2908 InNodes[0]->getNumTypes() == 1 &&
2909 "FIXME: cannot name multiple result nodes yet");
2910 MadeChange |= Node->UpdateNodeType(0, InNodes[0]->getExtType(0),
2911 *this);
2912 }
2913 }
2914
2915 // If there are multiple nodes with the same name, they must all have the
2916 // same type.
2917 if (Entry.second.size() > 1) {
2918 for (unsigned i = 0, e = Nodes.size()-1; i != e; ++i) {
2919 TreePatternNode *N1 = Nodes[i], *N2 = Nodes[i+1];
2920 assert(N1->getNumTypes() == 1 && N2->getNumTypes() == 1 &&
2921 "FIXME: cannot name multiple result nodes yet");
2922
2923 MadeChange |= N1->UpdateNodeType(0, N2->getExtType(0), *this);
2924 MadeChange |= N2->UpdateNodeType(0, N1->getExtType(0), *this);
2925 }
2926 }
2927 }
2928 }
2929
2930 bool HasUnresolvedTypes = false;
2931 for (const TreePatternNodePtr &Tree : Trees)
2932 HasUnresolvedTypes |= Tree->ContainsUnresolvedType(*this);
2933 return !HasUnresolvedTypes;
2934}

2936void TreePattern::print(raw_ostream &OS) const {
2937 OS << getRecord()->getName();
2938 if (!Args.empty()) {
2939 OS << "(" << Args[0];
2940 for (unsigned i = 1, e = Args.size(); i != e; ++i)
2941 OS << ", " << Args[i];
2942 OS << ")";
2943 }
2944 OS << ": ";
2945
2946 if (Trees.size() > 1)
2947 OS << "[\n";
2948 for (const TreePatternNodePtr &Tree : Trees) {

2951 OS << "\n";
2952 }
2953
2954 if (Trees.size() > 1)
2955 OS << "]\n";
2956}

2964CodeGenDAGPatterns::CodeGenDAGPatterns(RecordKeeper &R,
2965 PatternRewriterFn PatternRewriter)
2966 : Records(R), Target(R), LegalVTS(Target.getLegalValueTypes()),
2967 PatternRewriter(PatternRewriter) {
2968
2969 // If the target declares a class called SupportsFatPointers, then we enable
2970 // support for two types of pointer.
2971 FatPointers = R.getClass("SupportsFatPointers");
2972
2973 Intrinsics = CodeGenIntrinsicTable(Records, false);
2974 TgtIntrinsics = CodeGenIntrinsicTable(Records, true);
2975 ParseNodeInfo();
2976 ParseNodeTransforms();
2977 ParseComplexPatterns();
2978 ParsePatternFragments();
2979 ParseDefaultOperands();
2980 ParseInstructions();
2981 ParsePatternFragments(/*OutFrags*/true);
2982 ParsePatterns();
2983
2984 // Break patterns with parameterized types into a series of patterns,
2985 // where each one has a fixed type and is predicated on the conditions
2986 // of the associated HW mode.
2987 ExpandHwModeBasedTypes();
2988
2989 // Generate variants. For example, commutative patterns can match
2990 // multiple ways. Add them to PatternsToMatch as well.
2991 GenerateVariants();
2992
2993 // Infer instruction flags. For example, we can detect loads,
2994 // stores, and side effects in many cases by examining an
2995 // instruction's pattern.
2996 InferInstructionFlags();
2997
2998 // Verify that instruction flags match the patterns.
2999 VerifyInstructionFlags();
3000}

3010// Parse all of the SDNode definitions for the target, populating SDNodes.
3011void CodeGenDAGPatterns::ParseNodeInfo() {
3012 std::vector<Record*> Nodes = Records.getAllDerivedDefinitions("SDNode");
3013 const CodeGenHwModes &CGH = getTargetInfo().getHwModes();
3014
3015 while (!Nodes.empty()) {
3016 Record *R = Nodes.back();
3017 SDNodes.insert(std::make_pair(R, SDNodeInfo(R, CGH)));
3018 Nodes.pop_back();
3019 }
3020
3021 // Get the builtin intrinsic nodes.
3022 intrinsic_void_sdnode = getSDNodeNamed("intrinsic_void");
3023 intrinsic_w_chain_sdnode = getSDNodeNamed("intrinsic_w_chain");
3024 intrinsic_wo_chain_sdnode = getSDNodeNamed("intrinsic_wo_chain");
3025}

3027/// ParseNodeTransforms - Parse all SDNodeXForm instances into the SDNodeXForms
3028/// map, and emit them to the file as functions.
3029void CodeGenDAGPatterns::ParseNodeTransforms() {
3030 std::vector<Record*> Xforms = Records.getAllDerivedDefinitions("SDNodeXForm");
3031 while (!Xforms.empty()) {
3032 Record *XFormNode = Xforms.back();
3033 Record *SDNode = XFormNode->getValueAsDef("Opcode");
3034 StringRef Code = XFormNode->getValueAsString("XFormFunction");
3035 SDNodeXForms.insert(std::make_pair(XFormNode, NodeXForm(SDNode, Code)));
3036
3037 Xforms.pop_back();
3038 }

3041void CodeGenDAGPatterns::ParseComplexPatterns() {
3042 std::vector<Record*> AMs = Records.getAllDerivedDefinitions("ComplexPattern");
3043 while (!AMs.empty()) {
3044 ComplexPatterns.insert(std::make_pair(AMs.back(), AMs.back()));
3045 AMs.pop_back();
3046 }

3049
3050/// ParsePatternFragments - Parse all of the PatFrag definitions in the .td
3051/// file, building up the PatternFragments map. After we've collected them all,
3052/// inline fragments together as necessary, so that there are no references left
3053/// inside a pattern fragment to a pattern fragment.
3054///
3055void CodeGenDAGPatterns::ParsePatternFragments(bool OutFrags) {
3056 std::vector<Record*> Fragments = Records.getAllDerivedDefinitions("PatFrags");
3057
3058 // First step, parse all of the fragments.
3059 for (Record *Frag : Fragments) {
3060 if (OutFrags != Frag->isSubClassOf("OutPatFrag"))
3061 continue;
3062
3063 ListInit *LI = Frag->getValueAsListInit("Fragments");
3064 TreePattern *P =
3065 (PatternFragments[Frag] = llvm::make_unique<TreePattern>(
3066 Frag, LI, !Frag->isSubClassOf("OutPatFrag"),
3067 *this)).get();
3068
3069 // Validate the argument list, converting it to set, to discard duplicates.
3070 std::vector<std::string> &Args = P->getArgList();
3071 // Copy the args so we can take StringRefs to them.
3072 auto ArgsCopy = Args;
3073 SmallDenseSet<StringRef, 4> OperandsSet;
3074 OperandsSet.insert(ArgsCopy.begin(), ArgsCopy.end());
3075
3076 if (OperandsSet.count(""))
3077 P->error("Cannot have unnamed 'node' values in pattern fragment!");
3078
3079 // Parse the operands list.
3080 DagInit *OpsList = Frag->getValueAsDag("Operands");
3081 DefInit *OpsOp = dyn_cast<DefInit>(OpsList->getOperator());
3082 // Special cases: ops == outs == ins. Different names are used to
3083 // improve readability.
3084 if (!OpsOp ||
3085 (OpsOp->getDef()->getName() != "ops" &&
3086 OpsOp->getDef()->getName() != "outs" &&
3087 OpsOp->getDef()->getName() != "ins"))
3088 P->error("Operands list should start with '(ops ... '!");
3089
3090 // Copy over the arguments.
3091 Args.clear();
3092 for (unsigned j = 0, e = OpsList->getNumArgs(); j != e; ++j) {
3093 if (!isa<DefInit>(OpsList->getArg(j)) ||
3094 cast<DefInit>(OpsList->getArg(j))->getDef()->getName() != "node")
3095 P->error("Operands list should all be 'node' values.");
3096 if (!OpsList->getArgName(j))
3097 P->error("Operands list should have names for each operand!");
3098 StringRef ArgNameStr = OpsList->getArgNameStr(j);
3099 if (!OperandsSet.count(ArgNameStr))
3100 P->error("'" + ArgNameStr +
3101 "' does not occur in pattern or was multiply specified!");
3102 OperandsSet.erase(ArgNameStr);
3103 Args.push_back(ArgNameStr);
3104 }
3105
3106 if (!OperandsSet.empty())
3107 P->error("Operands list does not contain an entry for operand '" +
3108 *OperandsSet.begin() + "'!");
3109
3110 // If there is a node transformation corresponding to this, keep track of
3111 // it.
3112 Record *Transform = Frag->getValueAsDef("OperandTransform");
3113 if (!getSDNodeTransform(Transform).second.empty()) // not noop xform?
3114 for (auto T : P->getTrees())
3115 T->setTransformFn(Transform);
3116 }
3117
3118 // Now that we've parsed all of the tree fragments, do a closure on them so
3119 // that there are not references to PatFrags left inside of them.
3120 for (Record *Frag : Fragments) {
3121 if (OutFrags != Frag->isSubClassOf("OutPatFrag"))
3122 continue;
3123
3124 TreePattern &ThePat = *PatternFragments[Frag];
3125 ThePat.InlinePatternFragments();
3126
3127 // Infer as many types as possible. Don't worry about it if we don't infer
3128 // all of them, some may depend on the inputs of the pattern. Also, don't
3129 // validate type sets; validation may cause spurious failures e.g. if a
3130 // fragment needs floating-point types but the current target does not have
3131 // any (this is only an error if that fragment is ever used!).
3132 {
3133 TypeInfer::SuppressValidation SV(ThePat.getInfer());
3134 ThePat.InferAllTypes();
3135 ThePat.resetError();
3136 }
3137
3138 // If debugging, print out the pattern fragment result.
3139 LLVM_DEBUG(ThePat.dump());
3140 }
3141}
3142
3143void CodeGenDAGPatterns::ParseDefaultOperands() {
3144 std::vector<Record*> DefaultOps;
3145 DefaultOps = Records.getAllDerivedDefinitions("OperandWithDefaultOps");
3146
3147 // Find some SDNode.
3148 assert(!SDNodes.empty() && "No SDNodes parsed?");
3149 Init *SomeSDNode = DefInit::get(SDNodes.begin()->first);
3150
3151 for (unsigned i = 0, e = DefaultOps.size(); i != e; ++i) {
3152 DagInit *DefaultInfo = DefaultOps[i]->getValueAsDag("DefaultOps");
3153
3154 // Clone the DefaultInfo dag node, changing the operator from 'ops' to
3155 // SomeSDnode so that we can parse this.
3156 std::vector<std::pair<Init*, StringInit*> > Ops;
3157 for (unsigned op = 0, e = DefaultInfo->getNumArgs(); op != e; ++op)
3158 Ops.push_back(std::make_pair(DefaultInfo->getArg(op),
3159 DefaultInfo->getArgName(op)));
3160 DagInit *DI = DagInit::get(SomeSDNode, nullptr, Ops);
3161
3162 // Create a TreePattern to parse this.
3163 TreePattern P(DefaultOps[i], DI, false, *this);
3164 assert(P.getNumTrees() == 1 && "This ctor can only produce one tree!");
3165
3166 // Copy the operands over into a DAGDefaultOperand.
3167 DAGDefaultOperand DefaultOpInfo;
3168
3169 const TreePatternNodePtr &T = P.getTree(0);
3170 for (unsigned op = 0, e = T->getNumChildren(); op != e; ++op) {
3171 TreePatternNodePtr TPN = T->getChildShared(op);
3172 while (TPN->ApplyTypeConstraints(P, false))
3173 /* Resolve all types */;
3174
3175 if (TPN->ContainsUnresolvedType(P)) {
3176 PrintFatalError("Value #" + Twine(i) + " of OperandWithDefaultOps '" +
3177 DefaultOps[i]->getName() +
3178 "' doesn't have a concrete type!");
3179 }
3180 DefaultOpInfo.DefaultOps.push_back(std::move(TPN));
3181 }
3182
3183 // Insert it into the DefaultOperands map so we can find it later.
3184 DefaultOperands[DefaultOps[i]] = DefaultOpInfo;
3185 }
3186}
3187
3188/// HandleUse - Given "Pat" a leaf in the pattern, check to see if it is an
3189/// instruction input. Return true if this is a real use.
3190static bool HandleUse(TreePattern &I, TreePatternNodePtr Pat,
3191 std::map<std::string, TreePatternNodePtr> &InstInputs) {
3192 // No name -> not interesting.
3193 if (Pat->getName().empty()) {
3194 if (Pat->isLeaf()) {
3195 DefInit *DI = dyn_cast<DefInit>(Pat->getLeafValue());
3196 if (DI && (DI->getDef()->isSubClassOf("RegisterClass") ||
3197 DI->getDef()->isSubClassOf("RegisterOperand")))
3198 I.error("Input " + DI->getDef()->getName() + " must be named!");
3199 }
3200 return false;
3201 }
3202
3203 Record *Rec;
3204 if (Pat->isLeaf()) {
3205 DefInit *DI = dyn_cast<DefInit>(Pat->getLeafValue());
3206 if (!DI)
3207 I.error("Input $" + Pat->getName() + " must be an identifier!");
3208 Rec = DI->getDef();
3209 } else {
3210 Rec = Pat->getOperator();
3211 }
3212
3213 // SRCVALUE nodes are ignored.
3214 if (Rec->getName() == "srcvalue")
3215 return false;
3216
3217 TreePatternNodePtr &Slot = InstInputs[Pat->getName()];
3218 if (!Slot) {
3219 Slot = Pat;
3220 return true;
3221 }
3222 Record *SlotRec;
3223 if (Slot->isLeaf()) {
3224 SlotRec = cast<DefInit>(Slot->getLeafValue())->getDef();
3225 } else {
3226 assert(Slot->getNumChildren() == 0 && "can't be a use with children!");
3227 SlotRec = Slot->getOperator();
3228 }
3229
3230 // Ensure that the inputs agree if we've already seen this input.
3231 if (Rec != SlotRec)
3232 I.error("All $" + Pat->getName() + " inputs must agree with each other");
3233 // Ensure that the types can agree as well.
3234 Slot->UpdateNodeType(0, Pat->getExtType(0), I);
3235 Pat->UpdateNodeType(0, Slot->getExtType(0), I);
3236 if (Slot->getExtTypes() != Pat->getExtTypes())
3237 I.error("All $" + Pat->getName() + " inputs must agree with each other");
3238 return true;
3239}
3240
3241/// FindPatternInputsAndOutputs - Scan the specified TreePatternNode (which is
3242/// part of "I", the instruction), computing the set of inputs and outputs of
3243/// the pattern. Report errors if we see anything naughty.
3244void CodeGenDAGPatterns::FindPatternInputsAndOutputs(
3245 TreePattern &I, TreePatternNodePtr Pat,
3246 std::map<std::string, TreePatternNodePtr> &InstInputs,
3247 MapVector<std::string, TreePatternNodePtr, std::map<std::string, unsigned>>
3248 &InstResults,
3249 std::vector<Record *> &InstImpResults) {
3250
3251 // The instruction pattern still has unresolved fragments. For *named*
3252 // nodes we must resolve those here. This may not result in multiple
3253 // alternatives.
3254 if (!Pat->getName().empty()) {
3255 TreePattern SrcPattern(I.getRecord(), Pat, true, *this);
3256 SrcPattern.InlinePatternFragments();
3257 SrcPattern.InferAllTypes();
3258 Pat = SrcPattern.getOnlyTree();
3259 }
3260
3261 if (Pat->isLeaf()) {
3262 bool isUse = HandleUse(I, Pat, InstInputs);
3263 if (!isUse && Pat->getTransformFn())
3264 I.error("Cannot specify a transform function for a non-input value!");
3265 return;
3266 }
3267
3268 if (Pat->getOperator()->getName() == "implicit") {
3269 for (unsigned i = 0, e = Pat->getNumChildren(); i != e; ++i) {
3270 TreePatternNode *Dest = Pat->getChild(i);
3271 if (!Dest->isLeaf())
3272 I.error("implicitly defined value should be a register!");
3273
3274 DefInit *Val = dyn_cast<DefInit>(Dest->getLeafValue());
3275 if (!Val || !Val->getDef()->isSubClassOf("Register"))
3276 I.error("implicitly defined value should be a register!");
3277 InstImpResults.push_back(Val->getDef());
3278 }
3279 return;
3280 }
3281
3282 if (Pat->getOperator()->getName() != "set") {
3283 // If this is not a set, verify that the children nodes are not void typed,
3284 // and recurse.
3285 for (unsigned i = 0, e = Pat->getNumChildren(); i != e; ++i) {
3286 if (Pat->getChild(i)->getNumTypes() == 0)
3287 I.error("Cannot have void nodes inside of patterns!");
3288 FindPatternInputsAndOutputs(I, Pat->getChildShared(i), InstInputs,
3289 InstResults, InstImpResults);
3290 }
3291
3292 // If this is a non-leaf node with no children, treat it basically as if
3293 // it were a leaf. This handles nodes like (imm).
3294 bool isUse = HandleUse(I, Pat, InstInputs);
3295
3296 if (!isUse && Pat->getTransformFn())
3297 I.error("Cannot specify a transform function for a non-input value!");
3298 return;
3299 }
3300
3301 // Otherwise, this is a set, validate and collect instruction results.
3302 if (Pat->getNumChildren() == 0)
3303 I.error("set requires operands!");
3304
3305 if (Pat->getTransformFn())
3306 I.error("Cannot specify a transform function on a set node!");
3307
3308 // Check the set destinations.
3309 unsigned NumDests = Pat->getNumChildren()-1;
3310 for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumDests; ++i) {
3311 TreePatternNodePtr Dest = Pat->getChildShared(i);
3312 // For set destinations we also must resolve fragments here.
3313 TreePattern DestPattern(I.getRecord(), Dest, false, *this);
3314 DestPattern.InlinePatternFragments();
3315 DestPattern.InferAllTypes();
3316 Dest = DestPattern.getOnlyTree();
3317
3318 if (!Dest->isLeaf())
3319 I.error("set destination should be a register!");
3320
3321 DefInit *Val = dyn_cast<DefInit>(Dest->getLeafValue());
3322 if (!Val) {
3323 I.error("set destination should be a register!");
3324 continue;
3325 }
3326
3327 if (Val->getDef()->isSubClassOf("RegisterClass") ||
3328 Val->getDef()->isSubClassOf("ValueType") ||
3329 Val->getDef()->isSubClassOf("RegisterOperand") ||
3330 Val->getDef()->isSubClassOf("PointerLikeRegClass")) {
3331 if (Dest->getName().empty())
3332 I.error("set destination must have a name!");
3333 if (InstResults.count(Dest->getName()))
3334 I.error("cannot set '" + Dest->getName() + "' multiple times");
3335 InstResults[Dest->getName()] = Dest;
3336 } else if (Val->getDef()->isSubClassOf("Register")) {
3337 InstImpResults.push_back(Val->getDef());
3338 } else {
3339 I.error("set destination should be a register!");
3340 }
3341 }
3342
3343 // Verify and collect info from the computation.
3344 FindPatternInputsAndOutputs(I, Pat->getChildShared(NumDests), InstInputs,
3345 InstResults, InstImpResults);
3346}

3352class InstAnalyzer {
3353 const CodeGenDAGPatterns &CDP;
3354public:
3355 bool hasSideEffects;
3356 bool mayStore;
3357 bool mayLoad;
3358 bool isBitcast;
3359 bool isVariadic;
3360 bool hasChain;
3361
3362 InstAnalyzer(const CodeGenDAGPatterns &cdp)
3363 : CDP(cdp), hasSideEffects(false), mayStore(false), mayLoad(false),
3364 isBitcast(false), isVariadic(false), hasChain(false) {}
3365
3366 void Analyze(const PatternToMatch &Pat) {
3367 const TreePatternNode *N = Pat.getSrcPattern();
3368 AnalyzeNode(N);
3369 // These properties are detected only on the root node.
3370 isBitcast = IsNodeBitcast(N);
3371 }
3372
3373private:
3374 bool IsNodeBitcast(const TreePatternNode *N) const {
3375 if (hasSideEffects || mayLoad || mayStore || isVariadic)
3376 return false;
3377
3378 if (N->isLeaf())
3379 return false;
3380 if (N->getNumChildren() != 1 || !N->getChild(0)->isLeaf())
3381 return false;
3382
3383 const SDNodeInfo &OpInfo = CDP.getSDNodeInfo(N->getOperator());
3384 if (OpInfo.getNumResults() != 1 || OpInfo.getNumOperands() != 1)
3385 return false;
3386 return OpInfo.getEnumName() == "ISD::BITCAST";
3387 }
3388
3389public:
3390 void AnalyzeNode(const TreePatternNode *N) {
3391 if (N->isLeaf()) {
3392 if (DefInit *DI = dyn_cast<DefInit>(N->getLeafValue())) {
3393 Record *LeafRec = DI->getDef();
3394 // Handle ComplexPattern leaves.
3395 if (LeafRec->isSubClassOf("ComplexPattern")) {
3396 const ComplexPattern &CP = CDP.getComplexPattern(LeafRec);
3397 if (CP.hasProperty(SDNPMayStore)) mayStore = true;
3398 if (CP.hasProperty(SDNPMayLoad)) mayLoad = true;
3399 if (CP.hasProperty(SDNPSideEffect)) hasSideEffects = true;
3400 }
3401 }
3402 return;
3403 }
3404
3405 // Analyze children.
3406 for (unsigned i = 0, e = N->getNumChildren(); i != e; ++i)
3407 AnalyzeNode(N->getChild(i));
3408
3409 // Notice properties of the node.
3410 if (N->NodeHasProperty(SDNPMayStore, CDP)) mayStore = true;
3411 if (N->NodeHasProperty(SDNPMayLoad, CDP)) mayLoad = true;
3412 if (N->NodeHasProperty(SDNPSideEffect, CDP)) hasSideEffects = true;
3413 if (N->NodeHasProperty(SDNPVariadic, CDP)) isVariadic = true;
3414 if (N->NodeHasProperty(SDNPHasChain, CDP)) hasChain = true;
3415
3416 if (const CodeGenIntrinsic *IntInfo = N->getIntrinsicInfo(CDP)) {
3417 // If this is an intrinsic, analyze it.
3418 if (IntInfo->ModRef & CodeGenIntrinsic::MR_Ref)
3419 mayLoad = true;// These may load memory.
3420
3421 if (IntInfo->ModRef & CodeGenIntrinsic::MR_Mod)
3422 mayStore = true;// Intrinsics that can write to memory are 'mayStore'.
3423
3424 if (IntInfo->ModRef >= CodeGenIntrinsic::ReadWriteMem ||
3425 IntInfo->hasSideEffects)
3426 // ReadWriteMem intrinsics can have other strange effects.
3427 hasSideEffects = true;
3428 }
3429 }
3430
3431};
3432
3433static bool InferFromPattern(CodeGenInstruction &InstInfo,
3434 const InstAnalyzer &PatInfo,
3435 Record *PatDef) {
3436 bool Error = false;
3437
3438 // Remember where InstInfo got its flags.
3439 if (InstInfo.hasUndefFlags())
3440 InstInfo.InferredFrom = PatDef;
3441
3442 // Check explicitly set flags for consistency.
3443 if (InstInfo.hasSideEffects != PatInfo.hasSideEffects &&
3444 !InstInfo.hasSideEffects_Unset) {
3445 // Allow explicitly setting hasSideEffects = 1 on instructions, even when
3446 // the pattern has no side effects. That could be useful for div/rem
3447 // instructions that may trap.
3448 if (!InstInfo.hasSideEffects) {
3449 Error = true;
3450 PrintError(PatDef->getLoc(), "Pattern doesn't match hasSideEffects = " +
3451 Twine(InstInfo.hasSideEffects));
3452 }
3453 }
3454
3455 if (InstInfo.mayStore != PatInfo.mayStore && !InstInfo.mayStore_Unset) {
3456 Error = true;
3457 PrintError(PatDef->getLoc(), "Pattern doesn't match mayStore = " +
3458 Twine(InstInfo.mayStore));
3459 }
3460
3461 if (InstInfo.mayLoad != PatInfo.mayLoad && !InstInfo.mayLoad_Unset) {
3462 // Allow explicitly setting mayLoad = 1, even when the pattern has no loads.
3463 // Some targets translate immediates to loads.
3464 if (!InstInfo.mayLoad) {
3465 Error = true;
3466 PrintError(PatDef->getLoc(), "Pattern doesn't match mayLoad = " +
3467 Twine(InstInfo.mayLoad));
3468 }
3469 }
3470
3471 // Transfer inferred flags.
3472 InstInfo.hasSideEffects |= PatInfo.hasSideEffects;
3473 InstInfo.mayStore |= PatInfo.mayStore;
3474 InstInfo.mayLoad |= PatInfo.mayLoad;
3475
3476 // These flags are silently added without any verification.
3477 // FIXME: To match historical behavior of TableGen, for now add those flags
3478 // only when we're inferring from the primary instruction pattern.
3479 if (PatDef->isSubClassOf("Instruction")) {
3480 InstInfo.isBitcast |= PatInfo.isBitcast;
3481 InstInfo.hasChain |= PatInfo.hasChain;
3482 InstInfo.hasChain_Inferred = true;
3483 }
3484
3485 // Don't infer isVariadic. This flag means something different on SDNodes and
3486 // instructions. For example, a CALL SDNode is variadic because it has the
3487 // call arguments as operands, but a CALL instruction is not variadic - it
3488 // has argument registers as implicit, not explicit uses.
3489
3490 return Error;
3491}
3492
3493/// hasNullFragReference - Return true if the DAG has any reference to the
3494/// null_frag operator.
3495static bool hasNullFragReference(DagInit *DI) {
3496 DefInit *OpDef = dyn_cast<DefInit>(DI->getOperator());
3497 if (!OpDef) return false;
3498 Record *Operator = OpDef->getDef();
3499
3500 // If this is the null fragment, return true.
3501 if (Operator->getName() == "null_frag") return true;
3502 // If any of the arguments reference the null fragment, return true.
3503 for (unsigned i = 0, e = DI->getNumArgs(); i != e; ++i) {
3504 DagInit *Arg = dyn_cast<DagInit>(DI->getArg(i));
3505 if (Arg && hasNullFragReference(Arg))
3506 return true;
3507 }
3508
3509 return false;
3510}
3511
3512/// hasNullFragReference - Return true if any DAG in the list references
3513/// the null_frag operator.
3514static bool hasNullFragReference(ListInit *LI) {
3515 for (Init *I : LI->getValues()) {
3516 DagInit *DI = dyn_cast<DagInit>(I);
3517 assert(DI && "non-dag in an instruction Pattern list?!");
3518 if (hasNullFragReference(DI))
3519 return true;
3520 }
3521 return false;
3522}

3524/// Get all the instructions in a tree.
3525static void
3526getInstructionsInTree(TreePatternNode *Tree, SmallVectorImpl<Record*> &Instrs) {
3527 if (Tree->isLeaf())
3528 return;
3529 if (Tree->getOperator()->isSubClassOf("Instruction"))
3530 Instrs.push_back(Tree->getOperator());
3531 for (unsigned i = 0, e = Tree->getNumChildren(); i != e; ++i)
3532 getInstructionsInTree(Tree->getChild(i), Instrs);
3533}

3535/// Check the class of a pattern leaf node against the instruction operand it
3536/// represents.
3537static bool checkOperandClass(CGIOperandList::OperandInfo &OI,
3538 Record *Leaf) {
3539 if (OI.Rec == Leaf)
3540 return true;
3541
3542 // Allow direct value types to be used in instruction set patterns.
3543 // The type will be checked later.
3544 if (Leaf->isSubClassOf("ValueType"))
3545 return true;
3546
3547 // Patterns can also be ComplexPattern instances.
3548 if (Leaf->isSubClassOf("ComplexPattern"))
3549 return true;
3550
3551 return false;
3552}
3553
3554void CodeGenDAGPatterns::parseInstructionPattern(
3555 CodeGenInstruction &CGI, ListInit *Pat, DAGInstMap &DAGInsts) {
3556
3557 assert(!DAGInsts.count(CGI.TheDef) && "Instruction already parsed!");
3558
3559 // Parse the instruction.
3560 TreePattern I(CGI.TheDef, Pat, true, *this);
3561
3562 // InstInputs - Keep track of all of the inputs of the instruction, along
3563 // with the record they are declared as.
3564 std::map<std::string, TreePatternNodePtr> InstInputs;
3565
3566 // InstResults - Keep track of all the virtual registers that are 'set'
3567 // in the instruction, including what reg class they are.
3568 MapVector<std::string, TreePatternNodePtr, std::map<std::string, unsigned>>
3569 InstResults;
3570
3571 std::vector<Record*> InstImpResults;
3572
3573 // Verify that the top-level forms in the instruction are of void type, and
3574 // fill in the InstResults map.
3575 SmallString<32> TypesString;
3576 for (unsigned j = 0, e = I.getNumTrees(); j != e; ++j) {
3577 TypesString.clear();
3578 TreePatternNodePtr Pat = I.getTree(j);
3579 if (Pat->getNumTypes() != 0) {
3580 raw_svector_ostream OS(TypesString);
3581 for (unsigned k = 0, ke = Pat->getNumTypes(); k != ke; ++k) {
3582 if (k > 0)
3583 OS << ", ";
3584 Pat->getExtType(k).writeToStream(OS);
3585 }
3586 I.error("Top-level forms in instruction pattern should have"
3587 " void types, has types " +
3588 OS.str());
3589 }
3590
3591 // Find inputs and outputs, and verify the structure of the uses/defs.
3592 FindPatternInputsAndOutputs(I, Pat, InstInputs, InstResults,
3593 InstImpResults);
3594 }
3595
3596 // Now that we have inputs and outputs of the pattern, inspect the operands
3597 // list for the instruction. This determines the order that operands are
3598 // added to the machine instruction the node corresponds to.
3599 unsigned NumResults = InstResults.size();
3600
3601 // Parse the operands list from the (ops) list, validating it.
3602 assert(I.getArgList().empty() && "Args list should still be empty here!");
3603
3604 // Check that all of the results occur first in the list.
3605 std::vector<Record*> Results;
3606 std::vector<unsigned> ResultIndices;
3607 SmallVector<TreePatternNodePtr, 2> ResNodes;
3608 for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumResults; ++i) {
3609 if (i == CGI.Operands.size()) {
3610 const std::string &OpName =
3611 std::find_if(InstResults.begin(), InstResults.end(),
3612 [](const std::pair<std::string, TreePatternNodePtr> &P) {
3613 return P.second;
3614 })
3615 ->first;
3616
3617 I.error("'" + OpName + "' set but does not appear in operand list!");
3618 }
3619
3620 const std::string &OpName = CGI.Operands[i].Name;
3621
3622 // Check that it exists in InstResults.
3623 auto InstResultIter = InstResults.find(OpName);
3624 if (InstResultIter == InstResults.end() || !InstResultIter->second)
3625 I.error("Operand $" + OpName + " does not exist in operand list!");
3626
3627 TreePatternNodePtr RNode = InstResultIter->second;
3628 Record *R = cast<DefInit>(RNode->getLeafValue())->getDef();
3629 ResNodes.push_back(std::move(RNode));
3630 if (!R)
3631 I.error("Operand $" + OpName + " should be a set destination: all "
3632 "outputs must occur before inputs in operand list!");
3633
3634 if (!checkOperandClass(CGI.Operands[i], R))
3635 I.error("Operand $" + OpName + " class mismatch!");
3636
3637 // Remember the return type.
3638 Results.push_back(CGI.Operands[i].Rec);
3639
3640 // Remember the result index.
3641 ResultIndices.push_back(std::distance(InstResults.begin(), InstResultIter));
3642
3643 // Okay, this one checks out.
3644 InstResultIter->second = nullptr;
3645 }
3646
3647 // Loop over the inputs next.
3648 std::vector<TreePatternNodePtr> ResultNodeOperands;
3649 std::vector<Record*> Operands;
3650 for (unsigned i = NumResults, e = CGI.Operands.size(); i != e; ++i) {
3651 CGIOperandList::OperandInfo &Op = CGI.Operands[i];
3652 const std::string &OpName = Op.Name;
3653 if (OpName.empty())
3654 I.error("Operand #" + Twine(i) + " in operands list has no name!");
3655
3656 if (!InstInputs.count(OpName)) {
3657 // If this is an operand with a DefaultOps set filled in, we can ignore
3658 // this. When we codegen it, we will do so as always executed.
3659 if (Op.Rec->isSubClassOf("OperandWithDefaultOps")) {
3660 // Does it have a non-empty DefaultOps field? If so, ignore this
3661 // operand.
3662 if (!getDefaultOperand(Op.Rec).DefaultOps.empty())
3663 continue;
3664 }
3665 I.error("Operand $" + OpName +
3666 " does not appear in the instruction pattern");
3667 }
3668 TreePatternNodePtr InVal = InstInputs[OpName];
3669 InstInputs.erase(OpName); // It occurred, remove from map.
3670
3671 if (InVal->isLeaf() && isa<DefInit>(InVal->getLeafValue())) {
3672 Record *InRec = static_cast<DefInit*>(InVal->getLeafValue())->getDef();
3673 if (!checkOperandClass(Op, InRec))
3674 I.error("Operand $" + OpName + "'s register class disagrees"
3675 " between the operand and pattern");
3676 }
3677 Operands.push_back(Op.Rec);
3678
3679 // Construct the result for the dest-pattern operand list.
3680 TreePatternNodePtr OpNode = InVal->clone();
3681
3682 // No predicate is useful on the result.
3683 OpNode->clearPredicateCalls();
3684
3685 // Promote the xform function to be an explicit node if set.
3686 if (Record *Xform = OpNode->getTransformFn()) {
3687 OpNode->setTransformFn(nullptr);
3688 std::vector<TreePatternNodePtr> Children;
3689 Children.push_back(OpNode);
3690 OpNode = std::make_shared<TreePatternNode>(Xform, std::move(Children),
3691 OpNode->getNumTypes());
3692 }
3693
3694 ResultNodeOperands.push_back(std::move(OpNode));
3695 }
3696
3697 if (!InstInputs.empty())
3698 I.error("Input operand $" + InstInputs.begin()->first +
3699 " occurs in pattern but not in operands list!");
3700
3701 TreePatternNodePtr ResultPattern = std::make_shared<TreePatternNode>(
3702 I.getRecord(), std::move(ResultNodeOperands),
3703 GetNumNodeResults(I.getRecord(), *this));
3704 // Copy fully inferred output node types to instruction result pattern.
3705 for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumResults; ++i) {
3706 assert(ResNodes[i]->getNumTypes() == 1 && "FIXME: Unhandled");
3707 ResultPattern->setType(i, ResNodes[i]->getExtType(0));
3708 ResultPattern->setResultIndex(i, ResultIndices[i]);
3709 }
3710
3711 // FIXME: Assume only the first tree is the pattern. The others are clobber
3712 // nodes.
3713 TreePatternNodePtr Pattern = I.getTree(0);
3714 TreePatternNodePtr SrcPattern;
3715 if (Pattern->getOperator()->getName() == "set") {
3716 SrcPattern = Pattern->getChild(Pattern->getNumChildren()-1)->clone();
3717 } else{
3718 // Not a set (store or something?)
3719 SrcPattern = Pattern;
3720 }
3721
3722 // Create and insert the instruction.
3723 // FIXME: InstImpResults should not be part of DAGInstruction.
3724 Record *R = I.getRecord();
3725 DAGInsts.emplace(std::piecewise_construct, std::forward_as_tuple(R),
3726 std::forward_as_tuple(Results, Operands, InstImpResults,
3727 SrcPattern, ResultPattern));
3728
3729 LLVM_DEBUG(I.dump());
3730}
3731
3732/// ParseInstructions - Parse all of the instructions, inlining and resolving
3733/// any fragments involved. This populates the Instructions list with fully
3734/// resolved instructions.
3735void CodeGenDAGPatterns::ParseInstructions() {
3736 std::vector<Record*> Instrs = Records.getAllDerivedDefinitions("Instruction");
3737
3738 for (Record *Instr : Instrs) {
3739 ListInit *LI = nullptr;
3740
3741 if (isa<ListInit>(Instr->getValueInit("Pattern")))
3742 LI = Instr->getValueAsListInit("Pattern");
3743
3744 // If there is no pattern, only collect minimal information about the
3745 // instruction for its operand list. We have to assume that there is one
3746 // result, as we have no detailed info. A pattern which references the
3747 // null_frag operator is as-if no pattern were specified. Normally this
3748 // is from a multiclass expansion w/ a SDPatternOperator passed in as
3749 // null_frag.
3750 if (!LI || LI->empty() || hasNullFragReference(LI)) {
3751 std::vector<Record*> Results;
3752 std::vector<Record*> Operands;
3753
3754 CodeGenInstruction &InstInfo = Target.getInstruction(Instr);
3755
3756 if (InstInfo.Operands.size() != 0) {
3757 for (unsigned j = 0, e = InstInfo.Operands.NumDefs; j < e; ++j)
3758 Results.push_back(InstInfo.Operands[j].Rec);
3759
3760 // The rest are inputs.
3761 for (unsigned j = InstInfo.Operands.NumDefs,
3762 e = InstInfo.Operands.size(); j < e; ++j)
3763 Operands.push_back(InstInfo.Operands[j].Rec);
3764 }
3765
3766 // Create and insert the instruction.
3767 std::vector<Record*> ImpResults;
3768 Instructions.insert(std::make_pair(Instr,
3769 DAGInstruction(Results, Operands, ImpResults)));
3770 continue; // no pattern.
3771 }
3772
3773 CodeGenInstruction &CGI = Target.getInstruction(Instr);
3774 parseInstructionPattern(CGI, LI, Instructions);
3775 }
3776
3777 // If we can, convert the instructions to be patterns that are matched!
3778 for (auto &Entry : Instructions) {
3779 Record *Instr = Entry.first;
3780 DAGInstruction &TheInst = Entry.second;
3781 TreePatternNodePtr SrcPattern = TheInst.getSrcPattern();
3782 TreePatternNodePtr ResultPattern = TheInst.getResultPattern();
3783
3784 if (SrcPattern && ResultPattern) {
3785 TreePattern Pattern(Instr, SrcPattern, true, *this);
3786 TreePattern Result(Instr, ResultPattern, false, *this);
3787 ParseOnePattern(Instr, Pattern, Result, TheInst.getImpResults());
3788 }
3789 }
3790}
3791
3792typedef std::pair<TreePatternNode *, unsigned> NameRecord;
3793
3794static void FindNames(TreePatternNode *P,
3795 std::map<std::string, NameRecord> &Names,
3796 TreePattern *PatternTop) {
3797 if (!P->getName().empty()) {
3798 NameRecord &Rec = Names[P->getName()];
3799 // If this is the first instance of the name, remember the node.
3800 if (Rec.second++ == 0)
3801 Rec.first = P;
3802 else if (Rec.first->getExtTypes() != P->getExtTypes())
3803 PatternTop->error("repetition of value: $" + P->getName() +
3804 " where different uses have different types!");
3805 }
3806
3807 if (!P->isLeaf()) {
3808 for (unsigned i = 0, e = P->getNumChildren(); i != e; ++i)
3809 FindNames(P->getChild(i), Names, PatternTop);
3810 }
3811}
3812
3813std::vector<Predicate> CodeGenDAGPatterns::makePredList(ListInit *L) {
3814 std::vector<Predicate> Preds;
3815 for (Init *I : L->getValues()) {
3816 if (DefInit *Pred = dyn_cast<DefInit>(I))
3817 Preds.push_back(Pred->getDef());
3818 else
3819 llvm_unreachable("Non-def on the list");
3820 }
3821
3822 // Sort so that different orders get canonicalized to the same string.
3823 llvm::sort(Preds);
3824 return Preds;
3825}
3826
3827void CodeGenDAGPatterns::AddPatternToMatch(TreePattern *Pattern,
3828 PatternToMatch &&PTM) {
3829 // Do some sanity checking on the pattern we're about to match.
3830 std::string Reason;
3831 if (!PTM.getSrcPattern()->canPatternMatch(Reason, *this)) {
3832 PrintWarning(Pattern->getRecord()->getLoc(),
3833 Twine("Pattern can never match: ") + Reason);
3834 return;
3835 }
3836
3837 // If the source pattern's root is a complex pattern, that complex pattern
3838 // must specify the nodes it can potentially match.
3839 if (const ComplexPattern *CP =
3840 PTM.getSrcPattern()->getComplexPatternInfo(*this))
3841 if (CP->getRootNodes().empty())
3842 Pattern->error("ComplexPattern at root must specify list of opcodes it"
3843 " could match");
3844
3845
3846 // Find all of the named values in the input and output, ensure they have the
3847 // same type.
3848 std::map<std::string, NameRecord> SrcNames, DstNames;
3849 FindNames(PTM.getSrcPattern(), SrcNames, Pattern);
3850 FindNames(PTM.getDstPattern(), DstNames, Pattern);
3851
3852 // Scan all of the named values in the destination pattern, rejecting them if
3853 // they don't exist in the input pattern.
3854 for (const auto &Entry : DstNames) {
3855 if (SrcNames[Entry.first].first == nullptr)
3856 Pattern->error("Pattern has input without matching name in output: $" +
3857 Entry.first);
3858 }
3859
3860 // Scan all of the named values in the source pattern, rejecting them if the
3861 // name isn't used in the dest, and isn't used to tie two values together.
3862 for (const auto &Entry : SrcNames)
3863 if (DstNames[Entry.first].first == nullptr &&
3864 SrcNames[Entry.first].second == 1)
3865 Pattern->error("Pattern has dead named input: $" + Entry.first);
3866
3867 PatternsToMatch.push_back(PTM);
3868}
3869
3870void CodeGenDAGPatterns::InferInstructionFlags() {
3871 ArrayRef<const CodeGenInstruction*> Instructions =
3872 Target.getInstructionsByEnumValue();
3873
3874 unsigned Errors = 0;
3875
3876 // Try to infer flags from all patterns in PatternToMatch. These include
3877 // both the primary instruction patterns (which always come first) and
3878 // patterns defined outside the instruction.
3879 for (const PatternToMatch &PTM : ptms()) {
3880 // We can only infer from single-instruction patterns, otherwise we won't
3881 // know which instruction should get the flags.
3882 SmallVector<Record*, 8> PatInstrs;
3883 getInstructionsInTree(PTM.getDstPattern(), PatInstrs);
3884 if (PatInstrs.size() != 1)
3885 continue;
3886
3887 // Get the single instruction.
3888 CodeGenInstruction &InstInfo = Target.getInstruction(PatInstrs.front());
3889
3890 // Only infer properties from the first pattern. We'll verify the others.
3891 if (InstInfo.InferredFrom)
3892 continue;
3893
3894 InstAnalyzer PatInfo(*this);
3895 PatInfo.Analyze(PTM);
3896 Errors += InferFromPattern(InstInfo, PatInfo, PTM.getSrcRecord());
3897 }
3898
3899 if (Errors)
3900 PrintFatalError("pattern conflicts");
3901
3902 // If requested by the target, guess any undefined properties.
3903 if (Target.guessInstructionProperties()) {
3904 for (unsigned i = 0, e = Instructions.size(); i != e; ++i) {
3905 CodeGenInstruction *InstInfo =
3906 const_cast<CodeGenInstruction *>(Instructions[i]);
3907 if (InstInfo->InferredFrom)
3908 continue;
3909 // The mayLoad and mayStore flags default to false.
3910 // Conservatively assume hasSideEffects if it wasn't explicit.
3911 if (InstInfo->hasSideEffects_Unset)
3912 InstInfo->hasSideEffects = true;
3913 }
3914 return;
3915 }
3916
3917 // Complain about any flags that are still undefined.
3918 for (unsigned i = 0, e = Instructions.size(); i != e; ++i) {
3919 CodeGenInstruction *InstInfo =
3920 const_cast<CodeGenInstruction *>(Instructions[i]);
3921 if (InstInfo->InferredFrom)
3922 continue;
3923 if (InstInfo->hasSideEffects_Unset)
3924 PrintError(InstInfo->TheDef->getLoc(),
3925 "Can't infer hasSideEffects from patterns");
3926 if (InstInfo->mayStore_Unset)
3927 PrintError(InstInfo->TheDef->getLoc(),
3928 "Can't infer mayStore from patterns");
3929 if (InstInfo->mayLoad_Unset)
3930 PrintError(InstInfo->TheDef->getLoc(),
3931 "Can't infer mayLoad from patterns");
3932 }
3933}
3934
3935
3936/// Verify instruction flags against pattern node properties.
3937void CodeGenDAGPatterns::VerifyInstructionFlags() {
3938 unsigned Errors = 0;
3939 for (ptm_iterator I = ptm_begin(), E = ptm_end(); I != E; ++I) {
3940 const PatternToMatch &PTM = *I;
3941 SmallVector<Record*, 8> Instrs;
3942 getInstructionsInTree(PTM.getDstPattern(), Instrs);
3943 if (Instrs.empty())
3944 continue;
3945
3946 // Count the number of instructions with each flag set.
3947 unsigned NumSideEffects = 0;
3948 unsigned NumStores = 0;
3949 unsigned NumLoads = 0;
3950 for (const Record *Instr : Instrs) {
3951 const CodeGenInstruction &InstInfo = Target.getInstruction(Instr);
3952 NumSideEffects += InstInfo.hasSideEffects;
3953 NumStores += InstInfo.mayStore;
3954 NumLoads += InstInfo.mayLoad;
3955 }
3956
3957 // Analyze the source pattern.
3958 InstAnalyzer PatInfo(*this);
3959 PatInfo.Analyze(PTM);
3960
3961 // Collect error messages.
3962 SmallVector<std::string, 4> Msgs;
3963
3964 // Check for missing flags in the output.
3965 // Permit extra flags for now at least.
3966 if (PatInfo.hasSideEffects && !NumSideEffects)
3967 Msgs.push_back("pattern has side effects, but hasSideEffects isn't set");
3968
3969 // Don't verify store flags on instructions with side effects. At least for
3970 // intrinsics, side effects implies mayStore.
3971 if (!PatInfo.hasSideEffects && PatInfo.mayStore && !NumStores)
3972 Msgs.push_back("pattern may store, but mayStore isn't set");
3973
3974 // Similarly, mayStore implies mayLoad on intrinsics.
3975 if (!PatInfo.mayStore && PatInfo.mayLoad && !NumLoads)
3976 Msgs.push_back("pattern may load, but mayLoad isn't set");
3977
3978 // Print error messages.
3979 if (Msgs.empty())
3980 continue;
3981 ++Errors;
3982
3983 for (const std::string &Msg : Msgs)
3984 PrintError(PTM.getSrcRecord()->getLoc(), Twine(Msg) + " on the " +
3985 (Instrs.size() == 1 ?
3986 "instruction" : "output instructions"));
3987 // Provide the location of the relevant instruction definitions.
3988 for (const Record *Instr : Instrs) {
3989 if (Instr != PTM.getSrcRecord())
3990 PrintError(Instr->getLoc(), "defined here");
3991 const CodeGenInstruction &InstInfo = Target.getInstruction(Instr);
3992 if (InstInfo.InferredFrom &&
3993 InstInfo.InferredFrom != InstInfo.TheDef &&
3994 InstInfo.InferredFrom != PTM.getSrcRecord())
3995 PrintError(InstInfo.InferredFrom->getLoc(), "inferred from pattern");
3996 }
3997 }
3998 if (Errors)
3999 PrintFatalError("Errors in DAG patterns");
4000}
4001
4002/// Given a pattern result with an unresolved type, see if we can find one
4003/// instruction with an unresolved result type. Force this result type to an
4004/// arbitrary element if it's possible types to converge results.
4005static bool ForceArbitraryInstResultType(TreePatternNode *N, TreePattern &TP) {
4006 if (N->isLeaf())
4007 return false;
4008
4009 // Analyze children.
4010 for (unsigned i = 0, e = N->getNumChildren(); i != e; ++i)
4011 if (ForceArbitraryInstResultType(N->getChild(i), TP))
4012 return true;
4013
4014 if (!N->getOperator()->isSubClassOf("Instruction"))
4015 return false;
4016
4017 // If this type is already concrete or completely unknown we can't do
4018 // anything.
4019 TypeInfer &TI = TP.getInfer();
4020 for (unsigned i = 0, e = N->getNumTypes(); i != e; ++i) {
4021 if (N->getExtType(i).empty() || TI.isConcrete(N->getExtType(i), false))
4022 continue;
4023
4024 // Otherwise, force its type to an arbitrary choice.
4025 if (TI.forceArbitrary(N->getExtType(i)))
4026 return true;
4027 }
4028
4029 return false;
4030}
4031
4032// Promote xform function to be an explicit node wherever set.
4033static TreePatternNodePtr PromoteXForms(TreePatternNodePtr N) {
4034 if (Record *Xform = N->getTransformFn()) {
4035 N->setTransformFn(nullptr);
4036 std::vector<TreePatternNodePtr> Children;
4037 Children.push_back(PromoteXForms(N));
4038 return std::make_shared<TreePatternNode>(Xform, std::move(Children),
4039 N->getNumTypes());
4040 }
4041
4042 if (!N->isLeaf())
4043 for (unsigned i = 0, e = N->getNumChildren(); i != e; ++i) {
4044 TreePatternNodePtr Child = N->getChildShared(i);
4045 N->setChild(i, PromoteXForms(Child));
4046 }
4047 return N;
4048}
4049
4050void CodeGenDAGPatterns::ParseOnePattern(Record *TheDef,
4051 TreePattern &Pattern, TreePattern &Result,
4052 const std::vector<Record *> &InstImpResults) {
4053
4054 // Inline pattern fragments and expand multiple alternatives.
4055 Pattern.InlinePatternFragments();
4056 Result.InlinePatternFragments();
4057
4058 if (Result.getNumTrees() != 1)
4059 Result.error("Cannot use multi-alternative fragments in result pattern!");
4060
4061 // Infer types.
4062 bool IterateInference;
4063 bool InferredAllPatternTypes, InferredAllResultTypes;
4064 do {
4065 // Infer as many types as possible. If we cannot infer all of them, we
4066 // can never do anything with this pattern: report it to the user.
4067 InferredAllPatternTypes =
4068 Pattern.InferAllTypes(&Pattern.getNamedNodesMap());
4069
4070 // Infer as many types as possible. If we cannot infer all of them, we
4071 // can never do anything with this pattern: report it to the user.
4072 InferredAllResultTypes =
4073 Result.InferAllTypes(&Pattern.getNamedNodesMap());
4074
4075 IterateInference = false;
4076
4077 // Apply the type of the result to the source pattern. This helps us
4078 // resolve cases where the input type is known to be a pointer type (which
4079 // is considered resolved), but the result knows it needs to be 32- or
4080 // 64-bits. Infer the other way for good measure.
4081 for (auto T : Pattern.getTrees())
4082 for (unsigned i = 0, e = std::min(Result.getOnlyTree()->getNumTypes(),
4083 T->getNumTypes());
4084 i != e; ++i) {
4085 IterateInference |= T->UpdateNodeType(
4086 i, Result.getOnlyTree()->getExtType(i), Result);
4087 IterateInference |= Result.getOnlyTree()->UpdateNodeType(
4088 i, T->getExtType(i), Result);
4089 }
4090
4091 // If our iteration has converged and the input pattern's types are fully
4092 // resolved but the result pattern is not fully resolved, we may have a
4093 // situation where we have two instructions in the result pattern and
4094 // the instructions require a common register class, but don't care about
4095 // what actual MVT is used. This is actually a bug in our modelling:
4096 // output patterns should have register classes, not MVTs.
4097 //
4098 // In any case, to handle this, we just go through and disambiguate some
4099 // arbitrary types to the result pattern's nodes.
4100 if (!IterateInference && InferredAllPatternTypes &&
4101 !InferredAllResultTypes)
4102 IterateInference =
4103 ForceArbitraryInstResultType(Result.getTree(0).get(), Result);
4104 } while (IterateInference);
4105
4106 // Verify that we inferred enough types that we can do something with the
4107 // pattern and result. If these fire the user has to add type casts.
4108 if (!InferredAllPatternTypes)
4109 Pattern.error("Could not infer all types in pattern!");
4110 if (!InferredAllResultTypes) {
4111 Pattern.dump();
4112 Result.error("Could not infer all types in pattern result!");
4113 }
4114
4115 // Promote xform function to be an explicit node wherever set.
4116 TreePatternNodePtr DstShared = PromoteXForms(Result.getOnlyTree());
4117
4118 TreePattern Temp(Result.getRecord(), DstShared, false, *this);
4119 Temp.InferAllTypes();
4120
4121 ListInit *Preds = TheDef->getValueAsListInit("Predicates");
4122 int Complexity = TheDef->getValueAsInt("AddedComplexity");
4123
4124 if (PatternRewriter)
4125 PatternRewriter(&Pattern);
4126
4127 // A pattern may end up with an "impossible" type, i.e. a situation
4128 // where all types have been eliminated for some node in this pattern.
4129 // This could occur for intrinsics that only make sense for a specific
4130 // value type, and use a specific register class. If, for some mode,
4131 // that register class does not accept that type, the type inference
4132 // will lead to a contradiction, which is not an error however, but
4133 // a sign that this pattern will simply never match.
4134 if (Temp.getOnlyTree()->hasPossibleType())
4135 for (auto T : Pattern.getTrees())
4136 if (T->hasPossibleType())
4137 AddPatternToMatch(&Pattern,
4138 PatternToMatch(TheDef, makePredList(Preds),
4139 T, Temp.getOnlyTree(),
4140 InstImpResults, Complexity,
4141 TheDef->getID()));
4142}
4143
4144void CodeGenDAGPatterns::ParsePatterns() {
4145 std::vector<Record*> Patterns = Records.getAllDerivedDefinitions("Pattern");
4146
4147 for (Record *CurPattern : Patterns) {
4148 DagInit *Tree = CurPattern->getValueAsDag("PatternToMatch");
4149
4150 // If the pattern references the null_frag, there's nothing to do.
4151 if (hasNullFragReference(Tree))
4152 continue;
4153
4154 TreePattern Pattern(CurPattern, Tree, true, *this);
4155
4156 ListInit *LI = CurPattern->getValueAsListInit("ResultInstrs");
4157 if (LI->empty()) continue; // no pattern.
4158
4159 // Parse the instruction.
4160 TreePattern Result(CurPattern, LI, false, *this);
4161
4162 if (Result.getNumTrees() != 1)
4163 Result.error("Cannot handle instructions producing instructions "
4164 "with temporaries yet!");
4165
4166 // Validate that the input pattern is correct.
4167 std::map<std::string, TreePatternNodePtr> InstInputs;
4168 MapVector<std::string, TreePatternNodePtr, std::map<std::string, unsigned>>
4169 InstResults;
4170 std::vector<Record*> InstImpResults;
4171 for (unsigned j = 0, ee = Pattern.getNumTrees(); j != ee; ++j)
4172 FindPatternInputsAndOutputs(Pattern, Pattern.getTree(j), InstInputs,
4173 InstResults, InstImpResults);
4174
4175 ParseOnePattern(CurPattern, Pattern, Result, InstImpResults);
4176 }
4177}

4179static void collectModes(std::set<unsigned> &Modes, const TreePatternNode *N) {
4180 for (const TypeSetByHwMode &VTS : N->getExtTypes())
4181 for (const auto &I : VTS)
4182 Modes.insert(I.first);
4183
4184 for (unsigned i = 0, e = N->getNumChildren(); i != e; ++i)
4185 collectModes(Modes, N->getChild(i));
4186}
4187
4188void CodeGenDAGPatterns::ExpandHwModeBasedTypes() {
4189 const CodeGenHwModes &CGH = getTargetInfo().getHwModes();
4190 std::map<unsigned,std::vector<Predicate>> ModeChecks;
4191 std::vector<PatternToMatch> Copy = PatternsToMatch;
4192 PatternsToMatch.clear();
4193
4194 auto AppendPattern = [this, &ModeChecks](PatternToMatch &P, unsigned Mode) {
4195 TreePatternNodePtr NewSrc = P.SrcPattern->clone();
4196 TreePatternNodePtr NewDst = P.DstPattern->clone();
4197 if (!NewSrc->setDefaultMode(Mode) || !NewDst->setDefaultMode(Mode)) {
4198 return;
4199 }
4200
4201 std::vector<Predicate> Preds = P.Predicates;
4202 const std::vector<Predicate> &MC = ModeChecks[Mode];
4203 Preds.insert(Preds.end(), MC.begin(), MC.end());
4204 PatternsToMatch.emplace_back(P.getSrcRecord(), Preds, std::move(NewSrc),
4205 std::move(NewDst), P.getDstRegs(),
4206 P.getAddedComplexity(), Record::getNewUID(),
4207 Mode);
4208 };
4209
4210 for (PatternToMatch &P : Copy) {
4211 TreePatternNodePtr SrcP = nullptr, DstP = nullptr;
4212 if (P.SrcPattern->hasProperTypeByHwMode())
4213 SrcP = P.SrcPattern;
4214 if (P.DstPattern->hasProperTypeByHwMode())
4215 DstP = P.DstPattern;
4216 if (!SrcP && !DstP) {
4217 PatternsToMatch.push_back(P);
4218 continue;
4219 }
4220
4221 std::set<unsigned> Modes;
4222 if (SrcP)
4223 collectModes(Modes, SrcP.get());
4224 if (DstP)
4225 collectModes(Modes, DstP.get());
4226
4227 // The predicate for the default mode needs to be constructed for each
4228 // pattern separately.
4229 // Since not all modes must be present in each pattern, if a mode m is
4230 // absent, then there is no point in constructing a check for m. If such
4231 // a check was created, it would be equivalent to checking the default
4232 // mode, except not all modes' predicates would be a part of the checking
4233 // code. The subsequently generated check for the default mode would then
4234 // have the exact same patterns, but a different predicate code. To avoid
4235 // duplicated patterns with different predicate checks, construct the
4236 // default check as a negation of all predicates that are actually present
4237 // in the source/destination patterns.
4238 std::vector<Predicate> DefaultPred;
4239
4240 for (unsigned M : Modes) {
4241 if (M == DefaultMode)
4242 continue;
4243 if (ModeChecks.find(M) != ModeChecks.end())
4244 continue;
4245
4246 // Fill the map entry for this mode.
4247 const HwMode &HM = CGH.getMode(M);
4248 ModeChecks[M].emplace_back(Predicate(HM.Features, true));
4249
4250 // Add negations of the HM's predicates to the default predicate.
4251 DefaultPred.emplace_back(Predicate(HM.Features, false));
4252 }
4253
4254 for (unsigned M : Modes) {
4255 if (M == DefaultMode)
4256 continue;
4257 AppendPattern(P, M);
4258 }
4259
4260 bool HasDefault = Modes.count(DefaultMode);
4261 if (HasDefault)
4262 AppendPattern(P, DefaultMode);
4263 }
4264}

4270 if (N->isLeaf()) {

4304
4305/// CombineChildVariants - Given a bunch of permutations of each child of the
4306/// 'operator' node, put them together in all possible ways.
4307static void CombineChildVariants(
4308 TreePatternNodePtr Orig,
4309 const std::vector<std::vector<TreePatternNodePtr>> &ChildVariants,
4310 std::vector<TreePatternNodePtr> &OutVariants, CodeGenDAGPatterns &CDP,
4311 const MultipleUseVarSet &DepVars) {
4312 // Make sure that each operand has at least one variant to choose from.
4313 for (const auto &Variants : ChildVariants)
4314 if (Variants.empty())
4315 return;
4316
4317 // The end result is an all-pairs construction of the resultant pattern.
4318 std::vector<unsigned> Idxs;
4319 Idxs.resize(ChildVariants.size());
4320 bool NotDone;
4321 do {
4322#ifndef NDEBUG
4323 LLVM_DEBUG(if (!Idxs.empty()) {
4324 errs() << Orig->getOperator()->getName() << ": Idxs = [ ";
4325 for (unsigned Idx : Idxs) {
4326 errs() << Idx << " ";
4327 }
4328 errs() << "]\n";
4329 });
4330#endif
4331 // Create the variant and add it to the output list.
4332 std::vector<TreePatternNodePtr> NewChildren;
4333 for (unsigned i = 0, e = ChildVariants.size(); i != e; ++i)
4334 NewChildren.push_back(ChildVariants[i][Idxs[i]]);
4335 TreePatternNodePtr R = std::make_shared<TreePatternNode>(
4336 Orig->getOperator(), std::move(NewChildren), Orig->getNumTypes());
4337
4338 // Copy over properties.
4339 R->setName(Orig->getName());
4340 R->setNamesAsPredicateArg(Orig->getNamesAsPredicateArg());
4341 R->setPredicateCalls(Orig->getPredicateCalls());
4342 R->setTransformFn(Orig->getTransformFn());
4343 for (unsigned i = 0, e = Orig->getNumTypes(); i != e; ++i)
4344 R->setType(i, Orig->getExtType(i));
4345
4346 // If this pattern cannot match, do not include it as a variant.
4347 std::string ErrString;
4348 // Scan to see if this pattern has already been emitted. We can get
4349 // duplication due to things like commuting:
4350 // (and GPRC:$a, GPRC:$b) -> (and GPRC:$b, GPRC:$a)
4351 // which are the same pattern. Ignore the dups.
4352 if (R->canPatternMatch(ErrString, CDP) &&
4353 none_of(OutVariants, [&](TreePatternNodePtr Variant) {
4354 return R->isIsomorphicTo(Variant.get(), DepVars);
4355 }))
4356 OutVariants.push_back(R);
4357
4358 // Increment indices to the next permutation by incrementing the
4359 // indices from last index backward, e.g., generate the sequence
4360 // [0, 0], [0, 1], [1, 0], [1, 1].
4361 int IdxsIdx;
4362 for (IdxsIdx = Idxs.size() - 1; IdxsIdx >= 0; --IdxsIdx) {
4363 if (++Idxs[IdxsIdx] == ChildVariants[IdxsIdx].size())
4364 Idxs[IdxsIdx] = 0;
4365 else
4366 break;
4367 }
4368 NotDone = (IdxsIdx >= 0);
4369 } while (NotDone);
4370}

4372/// CombineChildVariants - A helper function for binary operators.
4373///
4374static void CombineChildVariants(TreePatternNodePtr Orig,
4375 const std::vector<TreePatternNodePtr> &LHS,
4376 const std::vector<TreePatternNodePtr> &RHS,
4377 std::vector<TreePatternNodePtr> &OutVariants,
4378 CodeGenDAGPatterns &CDP,
4379 const MultipleUseVarSet &DepVars) {
4380 std::vector<std::vector<TreePatternNodePtr>> ChildVariants;
4381 ChildVariants.push_back(LHS);
4382 ChildVariants.push_back(RHS);
4383 CombineChildVariants(Orig, ChildVariants, OutVariants, CDP, DepVars);
4384}
4385
4386static void
4387GatherChildrenOfAssociativeOpcode(TreePatternNodePtr N,
4388 std::vector<TreePatternNodePtr> &Children) {
4389 assert(N->getNumChildren()==2 &&"Associative but doesn't have 2 children!");
4390 Record *Operator = N->getOperator();
4391
4392 // Only permit raw nodes.
4393 if (!N->getName().empty() || !N->getPredicateCalls().empty() ||
4394 N->getTransformFn()) {
4395 Children.push_back(N);
4396 return;
4397 }
4398
4399 if (N->getChild(0)->isLeaf() || N->getChild(0)->getOperator() != Operator)
4400 Children.push_back(N->getChildShared(0));
4401 else
4402 GatherChildrenOfAssociativeOpcode(N->getChildShared(0), Children);
4403
4404 if (N->getChild(1)->isLeaf() || N->getChild(1)->getOperator() != Operator)
4405 Children.push_back(N->getChildShared(1));
4406 else
4407 GatherChildrenOfAssociativeOpcode(N->getChildShared(1), Children);
4408}
