4410/// GenerateVariantsOf - Given a pattern N, generate all permutations we can of
4411/// the (potentially recursive) pattern by using algebraic laws.
4412///
4413static void GenerateVariantsOf(TreePatternNodePtr N,
4414 std::vector<TreePatternNodePtr> &OutVariants,
4415 CodeGenDAGPatterns &CDP,
4416 const MultipleUseVarSet &DepVars) {
4417 // We cannot permute leaves or ComplexPattern uses.
4418 if (N->isLeaf() || N->getOperator()->isSubClassOf("ComplexPattern")) {
4419 OutVariants.push_back(N);
4420 return;
4421 }
4422
4423 // Look up interesting info about the node.
4424 const SDNodeInfo &NodeInfo = CDP.getSDNodeInfo(N->getOperator());
4425
4426 // If this node is associative, re-associate.
4427 if (NodeInfo.hasProperty(SDNPAssociative)) {
4428 // Re-associate by pulling together all of the linked operators
4429 std::vector<TreePatternNodePtr> MaximalChildren;
4430 GatherChildrenOfAssociativeOpcode(N, MaximalChildren);
4431
4432 // Only handle child sizes of 3. Otherwise we'll end up trying too many
4433 // permutations.
4434 if (MaximalChildren.size() == 3) {
4435 // Find the variants of all of our maximal children.
4436 std::vector<TreePatternNodePtr> AVariants, BVariants, CVariants;
4437 GenerateVariantsOf(MaximalChildren[0], AVariants, CDP, DepVars);
4438 GenerateVariantsOf(MaximalChildren[1], BVariants, CDP, DepVars);
4439 GenerateVariantsOf(MaximalChildren[2], CVariants, CDP, DepVars);
4440
4441 // There are only two ways we can permute the tree:
4442 // (A op B) op C and A op (B op C)
4443 // Within these forms, we can also permute A/B/C.
4444
4445 // Generate legal pair permutations of A/B/C.
4446 std::vector<TreePatternNodePtr> ABVariants;
4447 std::vector<TreePatternNodePtr> BAVariants;
4448 std::vector<TreePatternNodePtr> ACVariants;
4449 std::vector<TreePatternNodePtr> CAVariants;
4450 std::vector<TreePatternNodePtr> BCVariants;
4451 std::vector<TreePatternNodePtr> CBVariants;
4452 CombineChildVariants(N, AVariants, BVariants, ABVariants, CDP, DepVars);
4453 CombineChildVariants(N, BVariants, AVariants, BAVariants, CDP, DepVars);
4454 CombineChildVariants(N, AVariants, CVariants, ACVariants, CDP, DepVars);
4455 CombineChildVariants(N, CVariants, AVariants, CAVariants, CDP, DepVars);
4456 CombineChildVariants(N, BVariants, CVariants, BCVariants, CDP, DepVars);
4457 CombineChildVariants(N, CVariants, BVariants, CBVariants, CDP, DepVars);
4458
4459 // Combine those into the result: (x op x) op x
4460 CombineChildVariants(N, ABVariants, CVariants, OutVariants, CDP, DepVars);
4461 CombineChildVariants(N, BAVariants, CVariants, OutVariants, CDP, DepVars);
4462 CombineChildVariants(N, ACVariants, BVariants, OutVariants, CDP, DepVars);
4463 CombineChildVariants(N, CAVariants, BVariants, OutVariants, CDP, DepVars);
4464 CombineChildVariants(N, BCVariants, AVariants, OutVariants, CDP, DepVars);
4465 CombineChildVariants(N, CBVariants, AVariants, OutVariants, CDP, DepVars);
4466
4467 // Combine those into the result: x op (x op x)
4468 CombineChildVariants(N, CVariants, ABVariants, OutVariants, CDP, DepVars);
4469 CombineChildVariants(N, CVariants, BAVariants, OutVariants, CDP, DepVars);
4470 CombineChildVariants(N, BVariants, ACVariants, OutVariants, CDP, DepVars);
4471 CombineChildVariants(N, BVariants, CAVariants, OutVariants, CDP, DepVars);
4472 CombineChildVariants(N, AVariants, BCVariants, OutVariants, CDP, DepVars);
4473 CombineChildVariants(N, AVariants, CBVariants, OutVariants, CDP, DepVars);
4474 return;
4475 }
4476 }
4477
4478 // Compute permutations of all children.
4479 std::vector<std::vector<TreePatternNodePtr>> ChildVariants;
4480 ChildVariants.resize(N->getNumChildren());
4481 for (unsigned i = 0, e = N->getNumChildren(); i != e; ++i)
4482 GenerateVariantsOf(N->getChildShared(i), ChildVariants[i], CDP, DepVars);
4483
4484 // Build all permutations based on how the children were formed.
4485 CombineChildVariants(N, ChildVariants, OutVariants, CDP, DepVars);
4486
4487 // If this node is commutative, consider the commuted order.
4488 bool isCommIntrinsic = N->isCommutativeIntrinsic(CDP);
4489 if (NodeInfo.hasProperty(SDNPCommutative) || isCommIntrinsic) {
4490 assert((N->getNumChildren()>=2 || isCommIntrinsic) &&
4491 "Commutative but doesn't have 2 children!");
4492 // Don't count children which are actually register references.
4493 unsigned NC = 0;
4494 for (unsigned i = 0, e = N->getNumChildren(); i != e; ++i) {
4495 TreePatternNode *Child = N->getChild(i);
4496 if (Child->isLeaf())
4497 if (DefInit *DI = dyn_cast<DefInit>(Child->getLeafValue())) {
4498 Record *RR = DI->getDef();
4499 if (RR->isSubClassOf("Register"))
4500 continue;
4501 }
4502 NC++;
4503 }
4504 // Consider the commuted order.
4505 if (isCommIntrinsic) {
4506 // Commutative intrinsic. First operand is the intrinsic id, 2nd and 3rd
4507 // operands are the commutative operands, and there might be more operands
4508 // after those.
4509 assert(NC >= 3 &&
4510 "Commutative intrinsic should have at least 3 children!");
4511 std::vector<std::vector<TreePatternNodePtr>> Variants;
4512 Variants.push_back(std::move(ChildVariants[0])); // Intrinsic id.
4513 Variants.push_back(std::move(ChildVariants[2]));
4514 Variants.push_back(std::move(ChildVariants[1]));
4515 for (unsigned i = 3; i != NC; ++i)
4516 Variants.push_back(std::move(ChildVariants[i]));
4517 CombineChildVariants(N, Variants, OutVariants, CDP, DepVars);
4518 } else if (NC == N->getNumChildren()) {
4519 std::vector<std::vector<TreePatternNodePtr>> Variants;
4520 Variants.push_back(std::move(ChildVariants[1]));
4521 Variants.push_back(std::move(ChildVariants[0]));
4522 for (unsigned i = 2; i != NC; ++i)
4523 Variants.push_back(std::move(ChildVariants[i]));
4524 CombineChildVariants(N, Variants, OutVariants, CDP, DepVars);
4525 }
4526 }
4527}

4530// GenerateVariants - Generate variants. For example, commutative patterns can
4531// match multiple ways. Add them to PatternsToMatch as well.
4532void CodeGenDAGPatterns::GenerateVariants() {
4533 LLVM_DEBUG(errs() << "Generating instruction variants.\n");
4534
4535 // Loop over all of the patterns we've collected, checking to see if we can
4536 // generate variants of the instruction, through the exploitation of
4537 // identities. This permits the target to provide aggressive matching without
4538 // the .td file having to contain tons of variants of instructions.
4539 //
4540 // Note that this loop adds new patterns to the PatternsToMatch list, but we
4541 // intentionally do not reconsider these. Any variants of added patterns have
4542 // already been added.
4543 //
4544 const unsigned NumOriginalPatterns = PatternsToMatch.size();
4545 BitVector MatchedPatterns(NumOriginalPatterns);
4546 std::vector<BitVector> MatchedPredicates(NumOriginalPatterns,
4547 BitVector(NumOriginalPatterns));
4548
4549 typedef std::pair<MultipleUseVarSet, std::vector<TreePatternNodePtr>>
4550 DepsAndVariants;
4551 std::map<unsigned, DepsAndVariants> PatternsWithVariants;
4552
4553 // Collect patterns with more than one variant.
4554 for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumOriginalPatterns; ++i) {
4555 MultipleUseVarSet DepVars;
4556 std::vector<TreePatternNodePtr> Variants;
4557 FindDepVars(PatternsToMatch[i].getSrcPattern(), DepVars);
4558 LLVM_DEBUG(errs() << "Dependent/multiply used variables: ");
4559 LLVM_DEBUG(DumpDepVars(DepVars));
4560 LLVM_DEBUG(errs() << "\n");
4561 GenerateVariantsOf(PatternsToMatch[i].getSrcPatternShared(), Variants,
4562 *this, DepVars);
4563
4564 assert(!Variants.empty() && "Must create at least original variant!");
4565 if (Variants.size() == 1) // No additional variants for this pattern.
4566 continue;
4567
4568 LLVM_DEBUG(errs() << "FOUND VARIANTS OF: ";
4569 PatternsToMatch[i].getSrcPattern()->dump(); errs() << "\n");
4570
4571 PatternsWithVariants[i] = std::make_pair(DepVars, Variants);
4572
4573 // Cache matching predicates.
4574 if (MatchedPatterns[i])
4575 continue;
4576
4577 const std::vector<Predicate> &Predicates =
4578 PatternsToMatch[i].getPredicates();
4579
4580 BitVector &Matches = MatchedPredicates[i];
4581 MatchedPatterns.set(i);
4582 Matches.set(i);
4583
4584 // Don't test patterns that have already been cached - it won't match.
4585 for (unsigned p = 0; p != NumOriginalPatterns; ++p)
4586 if (!MatchedPatterns[p])
4587 Matches[p] = (Predicates == PatternsToMatch[p].getPredicates());
4588
4589 // Copy this to all the matching patterns.
4590 for (int p = Matches.find_first(); p != -1; p = Matches.find_next(p))
4591 if (p != (int)i) {
4592 MatchedPatterns.set(p);
4593 MatchedPredicates[p] = Matches;
4594 }
4595 }
4596
4597 for (auto it : PatternsWithVariants) {
4598 unsigned i = it.first;
4599 const MultipleUseVarSet &DepVars = it.second.first;
4600 const std::vector<TreePatternNodePtr> &Variants = it.second.second;
4601
4602 for (unsigned v = 0, e = Variants.size(); v != e; ++v) {
4603 TreePatternNodePtr Variant = Variants[v];
4604 BitVector &Matches = MatchedPredicates[i];
4605
4606 LLVM_DEBUG(errs() << " VAR#" << v << ": "; Variant->dump();
4607 errs() << "\n");
4608
4609 // Scan to see if an instruction or explicit pattern already matches this.
4610 bool AlreadyExists = false;
4611 for (unsigned p = 0, e = PatternsToMatch.size(); p != e; ++p) {
4612 // Skip if the top level predicates do not match.
4613 if (!Matches[p])
4614 continue;
4615 // Check to see if this variant already exists.
4616 if (Variant->isIsomorphicTo(PatternsToMatch[p].getSrcPattern(),
4617 DepVars)) {
4618 LLVM_DEBUG(errs() << " *** ALREADY EXISTS, ignoring variant.\n");
4619 AlreadyExists = true;
4620 break;
4621 }
4622 }
4623 // If we already have it, ignore the variant.
4624 if (AlreadyExists) continue;
4625
4626 // Otherwise, add it to the list of patterns we have.
4627 PatternsToMatch.push_back(PatternToMatch(
4628 PatternsToMatch[i].getSrcRecord(), PatternsToMatch[i].getPredicates(),
4629 Variant, PatternsToMatch[i].getDstPatternShared(),
4630 PatternsToMatch[i].getDstRegs(),
4631 PatternsToMatch[i].getAddedComplexity(), Record::getNewUID()));
4632 MatchedPredicates.push_back(Matches);
4633
4634 // Add a new match the same as this pattern.
4635 for (auto &P : MatchedPredicates)
4636 P.push_back(P[i]);
4637 }
4638
4639 LLVM_DEBUG(errs() << "\n");
4640 }
